01:35:52,860 --> 01:35:54,660
if I wish thee well

2133
01:35:54,660 --> 01:35:55,600
of thy discovery.

2134
01:35:57,710 --> 01:35:58,610
Well then,

2135
01:35:58,750 --> 01:35:59,850
and thou hast reason,

2136
01:36:00,070 --> 01:36:01,610
by thy rational faculty,

2137
01:36:01,990 --> 01:36:03,770
stir up his rational faculty,

2138
01:36:04,030 --> 01:36:05,310
show him his error,

2139
01:36:05,790 --> 01:36:06,710
admonish him,

2140
01:36:06,870 --> 01:36:07,970
for if he listens,

2141
01:36:08,350 --> 01:36:09,430
thou wilt cure him,

2142
01:36:09,570 --> 01:36:11,090
and there is no need of anger,

2143
01:36:11,470 --> 01:36:13,050
as thou intendest to live

2144
01:36:13,050 --> 01:36:14,270
when thou art gone out.

2145
01:36:14,930 --> 01:36:15,970
So it is in thy

2146
01:36:15,970 --> 01:36:17,330
power to live here.

2147
01:36:18,800 --> 01:36:20,580
But if men do not permit thee,

2148
01:36:20,780 --> 01:36:22,320
then get away out of life,

2149
01:36:22,580 --> 01:36:23,580
yet so as if

2150
01:36:23,580 --> 01:36:25,300
thou wert suffering no harm.

2151
01:36:30,480 --> 01:36:31,820
Why dost thou think

2152
01:36:31,820 --> 01:36:33,020
that this is any trouble?

2153
01:36:33,680 --> 01:36:35,540
But so long as nothing of the kind

2154
01:36:35,540 --> 01:36:36,600
drives me out,

2155
01:36:37,000 --> 01:36:38,840
I remain, am free,

2156
01:36:39,260 --> 01:36:41,060
and no man shall hinder me

2157
01:36:41,060 --> 01:36:42,520
from doing what I choose.

2158
01:36:44,760 --> 01:36:45,980
And I choose to do

2159
01:36:45,980 --> 01:36:47,460
what is according to the nature

2160
01:36:47,460 --> 01:36:49,520
of the rational and social animal.

2161
01:36:50,230 --> 01:36:51,570
The intelligence of the universe

2162
01:36:51,570 --> 01:36:52,310
is social.

2163
01:36:53,070 --> 01:36:53,590
Accordingly,

2164
01:36:53,650 --> 01:36:55,110
it has made the inferior things

2165
01:36:55,110 --> 01:36:56,430
for the sake of the superior,

2166
01:36:56,730 --> 01:36:57,510
and it has fitted

2167
01:36:57,510 --> 01:36:58,870
the superior to one another.

2168
01:36:59,570 --> 01:37:01,190
Thou seest how it has

2169
01:37:01,190 --> 01:37:01,990
subordinated,

2170
01:37:02,570 --> 01:37:03,090
coordinated,

2171
01:37:03,090 --> 01:37:04,670
and assigned to everything

2172
01:37:04,670 --> 01:37:05,810
its proper portion,

2173
01:37:06,270 --> 01:37:07,190
and has brought together

2174
01:37:07,190 --> 01:37:08,930
into concord with one another

2175
01:37:08,930 --> 01:37:11,130
the things which are the best.

2176
01:37:11,590 --> 01:37:13,770
How hast thou behaved hitherto

2177
01:37:13,770 --> 01:37:15,650
to the gods, thy parents,

2178
01:37:16,090 --> 01:37:17,930
brethren, children, teachers,

2179
01:37:18,390 --> 01:37:20,670
to those who looked after thy infancy,

2180
01:37:20,970 --> 01:37:22,730
to thy friends, kinsfolk,

2181
01:37:23,070 --> 01:37:24,030
to thy slaves?

2182
01:37:27,340 --> 01:37:29,020
You need to add some text

2183
01:37:29,020 --> 01:37:29,980
for me to talk,

2184
01:37:30,340 --> 01:37:32,080
and call to recollection

2185
01:37:32,080 --> 01:37:33,480
both how many things

2186
01:37:33,480 --> 01:37:34,800
thou hast passed through,

2187
01:37:34,800 --> 01:37:36,160
and how many things

2188
01:37:36,160 --> 01:37:37,760
thou hast been able to endure,

2189
01:37:38,320 --> 01:37:39,860
and that the history of thy life

2190
01:37:39,860 --> 01:37:41,060
is now complete,

2191
01:37:41,180 --> 01:37:42,620
and thy service is ended,

2192
01:37:44,250 --> 01:37:45,950
and how many beautiful things

2193
01:37:45,950 --> 01:37:46,970
thou hast seen,

2194
01:37:47,730 --> 01:37:49,310
and how many pleasures

2195
01:37:49,310 --> 01:37:51,610
and pains thou hast despised,

2196
01:37:55,730 --> 01:37:56,410
spurned,

2197
01:37:59,630 --> 01:38:01,650
and to how many ill-minded folks

2198
01:38:01,650 --> 01:38:03,510
thou hast shown a kind disposition.

2199
01:38:05,140 --> 01:38:06,400
Why do unskilled

2200
01:38:06,400 --> 01:38:09,120
and ignorant souls disturb him

2201
01:38:09,120 --> 01:38:11,880
who has skill and knowledge?

2202
01:38:15,460 --> 01:38:19,490
Soul then has skill and knowledge.

2203
01:38:24,970 --> 01:38:26,670
Soon, very soon,

2204
01:38:26,970 --> 01:38:29,250
thou wilt be ashes or a skeleton,

2205
01:38:29,690 --> 01:38:31,650
and either a name or not even a name,

2206
01:38:32,030 --> 01:38:33,770
but name is sound and echo,

2207
01:38:34,430 --> 01:38:36,550
and the things which are much valued in life

2208
01:38:36,550 --> 01:38:39,030
are empty and rotten and trifling,

2209
01:38:39,370 --> 01:38:41,310
and like little dogs biting one another,

2210
01:38:41,510 --> 01:38:42,870
and little children quarreling,

2211
01:38:43,050 --> 01:38:44,950
laughing, and then straightway weeping.

2212
01:38:45,230 --> 01:38:46,990
But fidelity and modesty

2213
01:38:46,990 --> 01:38:48,450
and justice and truth

2214
01:38:48,450 --> 01:38:50,090
are fled up to Olympus

2215
01:38:50,090 --> 01:38:51,650
from the widespread earth.

2216
01:38:55,870 --> 01:38:58,390
If the objects of sense are easily changed

2217
01:38:58,390 --> 01:38:59,810
and never stand still,

2218
01:39:00,150 --> 01:39:02,130
and the organs of perception are dull

2219
01:39:02,130 --> 01:39:04,210
and easily receive false impressions,

2220
01:39:05,180 --> 01:39:06,720
and the poor soul itself

2221
01:39:06,720 --> 01:39:08,440
is an exhalation from blood,

2222
01:39:09,200 --> 01:39:10,600
but to have good repute

2223
01:39:10,600 --> 01:39:12,100
amidst such a world as this

2224
01:39:12,100 --> 01:39:13,100
is an empty thing,

2225
01:39:13,850 --> 01:39:15,670
why then dost thou not wait

2226
01:39:15,670 --> 01:39:17,630
in tranquility for thy end,

2227
01:39:18,170 --> 01:39:19,290
whether it is extinction

2228
01:39:19,290 --> 01:39:21,070
or removal to another state?

2229
01:39:25,210 --> 01:39:26,930
Why, what else than to venerate

2230
01:39:26,930 --> 01:39:28,430
gods and bless them,

2231
01:39:28,690 --> 01:39:29,950
and to do good to men,

2232
01:39:30,250 --> 01:39:31,470
and to practice tolerance

2233
01:39:31,470 --> 01:39:32,690
and self-restraint?

2234
01:39:33,460 --> 01:39:34,760
But as to everything

2235
01:39:34,760 --> 01:39:36,380
which is beyond the limits

2236
01:39:36,380 --> 01:39:37,980
of the poor flesh and breath,

2237
01:39:38,980 --> 01:39:41,080
to remember that this is neither thine

2238
01:39:41,080 --> 01:39:42,400
nor in thy power.

2239
01:39:42,760 --> 01:39:44,560
Thou canst pass thy life

2240
01:39:44,560 --> 01:39:46,280
in an equable flow of happiness,

2241
01:39:46,820 --> 01:39:48,940
if thou canst go by the right way

2242
01:39:48,940 --> 01:39:51,120
and think and act in the right way.

2243
01:39:51,460 --> 01:39:53,360
These two things are common,

2244
01:39:53,620 --> 01:39:54,960
both to the soul of God

2245
01:39:54,960 --> 01:39:56,360
and to the soul of man,

2246
01:39:56,360 --> 01:39:58,760
and to the soul of every rational being,

2247
01:39:59,160 --> 01:40:00,820
not to be hindered by another,

2248
01:40:01,570 --> 01:40:03,030
and to hold good to consist

2249
01:40:03,030 --> 01:40:04,810
in the disposition to justice,

2250
01:40:05,840 --> 01:40:06,740
practice of it,

2251
01:40:06,880 --> 01:40:08,960
and in this to let thy desire

2252
01:40:08,960 --> 01:40:10,360
find its termination.

2253
01:40:10,800 --> 01:40:12,920
If this is neither my own badness

2254
01:40:12,920 --> 01:40:14,940
nor an effect of my own badness,

2255
01:40:15,320 --> 01:40:17,200
and the common wheel is not injured,

2256
01:40:17,960 --> 01:40:19,740
on why am I troubled about it?

2257
01:40:22,090 --> 01:40:24,330
Do not be carried along inconsiderately

2258
01:40:24,330 --> 01:40:25,610
by the appearance of things,

2259
01:40:25,830 --> 01:40:27,090
but give help to all

2260
01:40:27,090 --> 01:40:28,330
according to thy ability

2261
01:40:28,330 --> 01:40:29,290
and their fitness,

2262
01:40:29,570 --> 01:40:31,190
and if they should have sustained loss.

2263
01:40:31,890 --> 01:40:33,690
In matters which are indifferent,

2264
01:40:34,330 --> 01:40:36,210
do not imagine this to be a damage,

2265
01:40:36,590 --> 01:40:37,810
for it is a bad habit.

2266
01:40:38,310 --> 01:40:40,470
But as the old man, when he went away,

2267
01:40:40,810 --> 01:40:42,590
asked back his foster child's top,

2268
01:40:42,970 --> 01:40:44,470
remembering that it was a top,

2269
01:40:44,990 --> 01:40:47,250
so do thou, in this case also.

2270
01:40:51,570 --> 01:40:53,510
Yes, but they are objects

2271
01:40:53,510 --> 01:40:55,230
of great concern to these people.

2272
01:40:55,710 --> 01:40:57,550
Wilt thou too then be made a fool

2273
01:40:57,550 --> 01:40:58,370
for these things?

2274
01:40:58,850 --> 01:41:00,710
I was once a fortunate man,

2275
01:41:00,790 --> 01:41:01,750
but I lost it,

2276
01:41:01,750 --> 01:41:02,950
I know not how.

2277
01:41:03,580 --> 01:41:05,540
But fortunate means that a man

2278
01:41:05,540 --> 01:41:07,800
has assigned to himself a good fortune,

2279
01:41:08,140 --> 01:41:09,020
and a good fortune

2280
01:41:09,020 --> 01:41:11,100
is good disposition of the soul,

2281
01:41:11,440 --> 01:41:13,460
good emotions, good actions.

2282
01:41:13,860 --> 01:41:14,720
Book 6

2283
01:41:14,720 --> 01:41:16,540
The substance of the universe

2284
01:41:16,540 --> 01:41:18,360
is obedient and compliant,

2285
01:41:18,680 --> 01:41:20,160
and the reason which governs it

2286
01:41:20,160 --> 01:41:23,140
has in itself no cause for doing evil,

2287
01:41:23,460 --> 01:41:24,960
for it has no malice,

2288
01:41:25,140 --> 01:41:26,980
nor does it do evil to anything,

2289
01:41:27,520 --> 01:41:29,440
nor is anything harmed by it.

2290
01:41:29,620 --> 01:41:31,860
But all things are made and perfected

2291
01:41:31,860 --> 01:41:32,980
according to this reason.

2292
01:41:33,620 --> 01:41:35,300
Let it make no difference to thee

2293
01:41:35,300 --> 01:41:37,160
whether thou art cold or warm,

2294
01:41:37,920 --> 01:41:39,640
if thou art doing thy duty,

2295
01:41:39,900 --> 01:41:41,660
and whether thou art drowsy

2296
01:41:41,660 --> 01:41:43,300
or satisfied with sleep,

2297
01:41:44,750 --> 01:41:46,350
and whether ill-spoken of

2298
01:41:46,350 --> 01:41:47,350
or praised.

2299
01:41:48,760 --> 01:41:50,660
For it is one of the acts of life,

2300
01:41:50,900 --> 01:41:52,480
this act by which we die,

2301
01:41:52,880 --> 01:41:54,440
it is sufficient then,

2302
01:41:54,800 --> 01:41:55,920
in this act also,

2303
01:41:56,060 --> 01:41:57,940
to do well what we have in hand.

2304
01:41:59,330 --> 01:42:00,130
Look within,

2305
01:42:02,160 --> 01:42:04,520
and all existing things soon change,

2306
01:42:04,520 --> 01:42:06,960
and they will either be reduced to vapor,

2307
01:42:07,420 --> 01:42:09,600
if indeed all substance is one,

2308
01:42:09,980 --> 01:42:11,460
or they will be dispersed.

2309
01:42:15,440 --> 01:42:16,780
The reason which governs

2310
01:42:16,780 --> 01:42:18,860
knows what its own disposition is

2311
01:42:18,860 --> 01:42:19,760
and what it does

2312
01:42:19,760 --> 01:42:21,540
and on what material it works.

2313
01:42:24,040 --> 01:42:25,960
The best way of avenging thyself

2314
01:42:25,960 --> 01:42:28,080
is not to become like the wrong-doer.

2315
01:42:29,140 --> 01:42:31,360
Take pleasure in one thing and rest in it

2316
01:42:31,360 --> 01:42:33,240
in passing from one social act

2317
01:42:33,240 --> 01:42:35,160
to another social act,

2318
01:42:35,260 --> 01:42:36,140
thinking of God.

2319
01:42:36,760 --> 01:42:37,860
The ruling principle

2320
01:42:37,860 --> 01:42:40,600
is that which rouses and turns itself,

2321
01:42:40,880 --> 01:42:43,020
and while it makes itself such as it is

2322
01:42:43,020 --> 01:42:44,700
and such as it wills to be,

2323
01:42:45,000 --> 01:42:46,580
it also makes everything which.

2324
01:42:47,160 --> 01:42:49,540
You need to add some text for me to talk.

2325
01:42:50,300 --> 01:42:52,540
In conformity to the nature of the universe

2326
01:42:52,540 --> 01:42:54,340
every single thing is accomplished,

2327
01:42:54,800 --> 01:42:56,980
for certainly it is not in conformity

2328
01:42:56,980 --> 01:42:58,160
to any other nature

2329
01:42:58,160 --> 01:42:59,960
that each thing is accomplished,

2330
01:43:00,440 --> 01:43:03,340
either a nature which externally comprehends this

2331
01:43:03,340 --> 01:43:05,340
or a nature which is comprehended

2332
01:43:05,340 --> 01:43:06,360
within this nature,

2333
01:43:06,360 --> 01:43:08,320
or a nature external,

2334
01:43:09,040 --> 01:43:10,520
and independent of this.

2335
01:43:10,940 --> 01:43:13,020
The universe is either a confusion

2336
01:43:13,020 --> 01:43:15,340
and a mutual involution of things

2337
01:43:15,340 --> 01:43:16,860
and a dispersion,

2338
01:43:17,200 --> 01:43:20,260
or it is unity and order and providence.

2339
01:43:20,800 --> 01:43:22,960
If, then, it is the former,

2340
01:43:23,280 --> 01:43:25,000
why do I desire to tarry

2341
01:43:25,000 --> 01:43:27,120
in a fortuitous combination of things

2342
01:43:27,120 --> 01:43:28,280
and such a disorder?

2343
01:43:28,640 --> 01:43:31,100
And why do I care about anything else

2344
01:43:31,100 --> 01:43:34,440
than how I shall at last become earth?

2345
01:43:38,350 --> 01:43:41,710
A now has been compelled by circumstances

2346
01:43:41,710 --> 01:43:43,610
to be disturbed in a manner.

2347
01:43:45,220 --> 01:43:47,420
Quickly return to thyself,

2348
01:43:47,500 --> 01:43:49,480
and do not continue out of tune

2349
01:43:49,480 --> 01:43:51,540
longer than the compulsion lasts,

2350
01:43:52,240 --> 01:43:54,400
for thou wilt have more mastery

2351
01:43:54,400 --> 01:43:55,300
over the harmony

2352
01:43:55,300 --> 01:43:57,620
by continually recurring to it.

2353
01:43:57,880 --> 01:43:59,780
If thou hadst a stepmother

2354
01:43:59,780 --> 01:44:01,680
and a mother at the same time,

2355
01:44:01,940 --> 01:44:04,440
thou wouldst be dutiful to thy stepmother,

2356
01:44:04,780 --> 01:44:06,640
but still thou wouldst

2357
01:44:06,640 --> 01:44:08,420
constantly return to thy mother.

2358
01:44:09,290 --> 01:44:11,150
Let the court and philosophy

2359
01:44:11,150 --> 01:44:12,410
now be to thee step.

2360
01:44:12,910 --> 01:44:15,070
Mother and mother return to philosophy

2361
01:44:15,070 --> 01:44:16,910
frequently and repose in her

2362
01:44:16,910 --> 01:44:19,070
through whom what thou meetest with

2363
01:44:19,070 --> 01:44:21,630
in the court appears to thee tolerable,

2364
01:44:21,870 --> 01:44:24,330
and thou appearst tolerable in the court.

2365
01:44:25,370 --> 01:44:27,490
You need to add some text for me to talk.

2366
01:44:29,990 --> 01:44:31,890
When we have meat before us,

2367
01:44:32,030 --> 01:44:33,190
and such eatables,

2368
01:44:33,510 --> 01:44:34,970
we receive the impression

2369
01:44:34,970 --> 01:44:37,750
that this is the dead body of a fish,

2370
01:44:38,130 --> 01:44:39,810
and this is the dead body

2371
01:44:39,810 --> 01:44:41,710
of a bird or of a pig.

2372
01:44:45,450 --> 01:44:50,800
And again, things themselves

2373
01:44:50,800 --> 01:44:52,100
and penetrate them,

2374
01:44:52,280 --> 01:44:54,680
and so we see what kind of things they are.

2375
01:44:55,230 --> 01:44:57,490
Just in the same way ought we to act

2376
01:44:57,490 --> 01:44:58,850
all through life,

2377
01:44:59,050 --> 01:45:00,310
and where there are things

2378
01:45:00,310 --> 01:45:02,890
which appear most worthy of our approbation,

2379
01:45:03,350 --> 01:45:04,850
we ought to lay them bare

2380
01:45:04,850 --> 01:45:06,690
and look at their worthlessness,

2381
01:45:07,110 --> 01:45:08,870
and strip them of all the words

2382
01:45:08,870 --> 01:45:10,330
by which they are exalted.

2383
01:45:10,910 --> 01:45:11,950
For outward show

2384
01:45:11,950 --> 01:45:14,230
is a wonderful perverter of the reason,

2385
01:45:14,230 --> 01:45:16,090
and when thou art most sure

2386
01:45:16,090 --> 01:45:17,170
that thou art employed

2387
01:45:17,170 --> 01:45:18,830
about things worth thy pains,

2388
01:45:19,550 --> 01:45:21,970
it is then that it cheats thee most.

2389
01:45:25,580 --> 01:45:27,200
Consider then what Crait says

2390
01:45:27,200 --> 01:45:28,620
of Xenocrates himself.

2391
01:45:29,120 --> 01:45:31,400
Most of the things which the multitude admire

2392
01:45:31,400 --> 01:45:32,940
are referred to objects

2393
01:45:32,940 --> 01:45:34,400
of the most general kind,

2394
01:45:34,740 --> 01:45:36,000
those which are held together

2395
01:45:36,000 --> 01:45:38,320
by cohesion or natural organization,

2396
01:45:38,660 --> 01:45:40,220
such as stones, wood,

2397
01:45:40,580 --> 01:45:42,400
fig-trees, vines, olives.

2398
01:45:42,640 --> 01:45:44,600
But those which are admired by men

2399
01:45:44,600 --> 01:45:46,140
who are a little more reasonable

2400
01:45:46,140 --> 01:45:47,600
are referred to the things

2401
01:45:47,600 --> 01:45:48,480
which are held together

2402
01:45:48,480 --> 01:45:49,720
by a living principle,

2403
01:45:50,140 --> 01:45:51,840
as flocks, herds.

2404
01:45:52,220 --> 01:45:54,320
Those which are admired by men

2405
01:45:54,320 --> 01:45:56,220
who are still more instructed

2406
01:45:56,220 --> 01:45:58,460
are the things which are held together

2407
01:45:58,460 --> 01:45:59,760
by a rational soul,

2408
01:46:00,100 --> 01:46:02,080
not, however, a universal soul,

2409
01:46:02,380 --> 01:46:04,960
but rational so far as it is a soul,

2410
01:46:05,680 --> 01:46:07,080
skilled in some art,

2411
01:46:07,360 --> 01:46:08,880
or expert in some other way,

2412
01:46:09,100 --> 01:46:10,220
or simply rational

2413
01:46:10,220 --> 01:46:11,800
so far as it possesses

2414
01:46:11,800 --> 01:46:12,840
a number of slaves.

2415
01:46:13,320 --> 01:46:15,020
You need to add some text

2416
01:46:15,020 --> 01:46:15,940
for me to talk.

2417
01:46:16,860 --> 01:46:19,080
But he who values rational soul,

2418
01:46:19,580 --> 01:46:20,740
a soul universal

2419
01:46:20,740 --> 01:46:22,720
and fitted for political life,

2420
01:46:23,200 --> 01:46:25,080
regards nothing else except this.

2421
01:46:25,600 --> 01:46:26,760
And above all things,

2422
01:46:26,960 --> 01:46:28,740
he keeps his soul in a condition

2423
01:46:28,740 --> 01:46:30,300
and in an activity,

2424
01:46:30,980 --> 01:46:33,220
conformable to reason and social life.

2425
01:46:33,690 --> 01:46:35,730
And he cooperates to this end

2426
01:46:35,730 --> 01:46:37,790
with those who are of the same kind

2427
01:46:37,790 --> 01:46:38,530
as himself.

2428
01:46:39,820 --> 01:46:41,880
Some things are hurrying into existence,

2429
01:46:42,320 --> 01:46:44,320
and others are hurrying out of it.

2430
01:46:44,580 --> 01:46:47,400
And of that which is coming into existence,

2431
01:46:48,400 --> 01:46:50,580
part is already extinguished

2432
01:46:50,580 --> 01:47:00,670
in this flowing stream then

2433
01:47:00,670 --> 01:47:02,410
on which there is no abiding

2434
01:47:02,410 --> 01:47:03,790
what is there of the things

2435
01:47:03,790 --> 01:47:04,810
which hurry by

2436
01:47:04,810 --> 01:47:07,110
on which a man would set a high price.

2437
01:47:08,260 --> 01:47:09,940
It would be just as if a man

2438
01:47:09,940 --> 01:47:10,920
should fall in love

2439
01:47:10,920 --> 01:47:12,080
with one of the sparrows

2440
01:47:12,080 --> 01:47:13,200
which fly by.

2441
01:47:14,820 --> 01:47:16,000
Something of this kind

2442
01:47:16,000 --> 01:47:17,760
is the very life of every man,

2443
01:47:18,700 --> 01:47:20,440
like the exhalation of the blood

2444
01:47:20,440 --> 01:47:22,240
and the respiration of the air.

2445
01:47:22,740 --> 01:47:24,280
For such as it is,

2446
01:47:24,300 --> 01:47:26,600
to have once drawn in the air,

2447
01:47:27,520 --> 01:47:29,180
and to have given it back,

2448
01:47:29,580 --> 01:47:31,460
which we do every moment.

2449
01:47:33,140 --> 01:47:34,780
Just the same is it

2450
01:47:34,780 --> 01:47:37,080
with the whole respiratory power

2451
01:47:37,080 --> 01:47:38,820
which thou didst receive

2452
01:47:38,820 --> 01:47:40,340
at thy birth yesterday

2453
01:47:40,340 --> 01:47:41,600
and the day before,

2454
01:47:45,800 --> 01:47:46,840
it back to the element

2455
01:47:46,840 --> 01:47:48,620
from which thou didst first draw it.

2456
01:47:49,100 --> 01:47:50,120
You need to add some text

2457
01:47:50,120 --> 01:47:51,020
for me to talk.

2458
01:47:51,840 --> 01:47:53,580
Neither is transpiration,

2459
01:47:53,820 --> 01:47:54,800
as in plants,

2460
01:47:55,140 --> 01:47:56,260
a thing to be valued,

2461
01:47:56,900 --> 01:47:58,120
nor respiration,

2462
01:47:58,120 --> 01:48:00,240
as in domesticated animals

2463
01:48:00,240 --> 01:48:01,520
and wild beasts,

2464
01:48:02,180 --> 01:48:04,020
nor the receiving of impressions

2465
01:48:04,020 --> 01:48:05,740
by the appearances of things,

2466
01:48:06,520 --> 01:48:08,320
nor being moved by desires

2467
01:48:08,320 --> 01:48:10,020
as puppets by strings,

2468
01:48:10,680 --> 01:48:12,460
nor assembling in herds,

2469
01:48:12,940 --> 01:48:15,040
nor in being nourished by food.

2470
01:48:15,640 --> 01:48:17,180
For this is just like

2471
01:48:17,180 --> 01:48:19,080
the act of separating and parting.

2472
01:48:19,620 --> 01:48:21,540
What then is worth being valued?

2473
01:48:22,380 --> 01:48:24,800
To be received with clapping of hands.

2474
01:48:32,100 --> 01:48:33,300
Neither must we value

2475
01:48:33,300 --> 01:48:34,560
the clapping of tongues

2476
01:48:34,560 --> 01:48:36,440
for the praise which comes from the many

2477
01:48:36,440 --> 01:48:37,860
is a clapping of tongues.

2478
01:48:40,250 --> 01:48:41,590
This, in my opinion,

2479
01:48:41,930 --> 01:48:43,150
to move thyself

2480
01:48:43,150 --> 01:48:44,450
and to restrain thyself

2481
01:48:44,450 --> 01:48:46,730
in conformity to thy proper constitution,

2482
01:48:47,130 --> 01:48:49,270
to which end both all employments

2483
01:48:49,270 --> 01:48:50,330
and arts lead.

2484
01:48:50,810 --> 01:48:52,350
For every art aims at this,

2485
01:48:52,670 --> 01:48:54,170
that the thing which has been made

2486
01:48:54,170 --> 01:48:55,530
should be adapted to the work

2487
01:48:55,530 --> 01:48:56,790
for which it has been made,

2488
01:48:57,070 --> 01:48:58,390
and both the vine-planter

2489
01:48:58,390 --> 01:48:59,630
who looks after the vine

2490
01:48:59,630 --> 01:49:00,810
and the horse-breaker.

2491
01:49:01,290 --> 01:49:02,250
But the education

2492
01:49:02,250 --> 01:49:03,630
and the teaching of youth

2493
01:49:03,630 --> 01:49:04,650
aim at something.

2494
01:49:07,150 --> 01:49:08,220
In this, then,

2495
01:49:08,300 --> 01:49:10,120
is the value of the education

2496
01:49:10,120 --> 01:49:11,120
and the teaching.

2497
01:49:13,760 --> 01:49:15,660
Then thou wilt be neither free

2498
01:49:15,660 --> 01:49:16,660
nor sufficient

2499
01:49:16,660 --> 01:49:18,260
for thy own happiness,

2500
01:49:18,620 --> 01:49:19,820
nor without passion.

2501
01:49:20,570 --> 01:49:21,770
For of necessity

2502
01:49:21,770 --> 01:49:23,370
thou must be envious,

2503
01:49:23,610 --> 01:49:23,990
jealous,

2504
01:49:24,230 --> 01:49:25,590
and suspicious of those

2505
01:49:25,590 --> 01:49:27,110
who can take away those things

2506
01:49:27,110 --> 01:49:28,690
and plot against those

2507
01:49:28,690 --> 01:49:31,090
who have that which is valued by thee.

2508
01:49:31,470 --> 01:49:33,030
Of necessity

2509
01:49:33,610 --> 01:49:35,410
a man must be altogether

2510
01:49:35,410 --> 01:49:37,550
in a state of perturbation

2511
01:49:37,550 --> 01:49:39,450
who wants any of these things,

2512
01:49:39,710 --> 01:49:40,530
and besides,

2513
01:49:40,870 --> 01:49:43,070
he must often find fault with the gods.

2514
01:49:44,180 --> 01:49:46,360
But to reverence and honor thy own mind

2515
01:49:46,360 --> 01:49:48,200
will make thee content with thyself

2516
01:49:48,200 --> 01:49:49,680
and in harmony with society

2517
01:49:49,680 --> 01:49:51,220
and in agreement with the gods,

2518
01:49:51,660 --> 01:49:53,380
that is, praising all that they give

2519
01:49:53,380 --> 01:49:54,120
and have ordered.

2520
01:49:54,700 --> 01:49:57,100
Above, below, all around

2521
01:49:57,100 --> 01:49:58,600
are the movements of the elements.

2522
01:50:00,440 --> 01:50:01,960
But the motion of virtue

2523
01:50:01,960 --> 01:50:03,080
is in none of these.

2524
01:50:03,580 --> 01:50:05,020
It is something more divine,

2525
01:50:05,360 --> 01:50:06,600
and advancing by a way

2526
01:50:06,600 --> 01:50:07,560
hardly observed,

2527
01:50:07,560 --> 01:50:09,400
it goes happily on its road,

2528
01:50:09,640 --> 01:50:11,820
how strangely men act.

2529
01:50:13,220 --> 01:50:14,420
They will not praise those

2530
01:50:14,420 --> 01:50:15,840
who are living at the same time

2531
01:50:15,840 --> 01:50:17,680
and living with and themselves.

2532
01:50:19,180 --> 01:50:21,520
But to be themselves,

2533
01:50:25,730 --> 01:50:28,800
but to be themselves

2534
01:50:28,870 --> 01:50:30,950
praised by posterity,

2535
01:50:31,470 --> 01:50:33,210
by those whom they have never seen

2536
01:50:33,210 --> 01:50:34,430
or ever will see,

2537
01:50:34,990 --> 01:50:36,830
this they set much value on.

2538
01:50:37,340 --> 01:50:39,080
But this is very much the same

2539
01:50:39,080 --> 01:50:40,920
as if thou shouldest be grieved

2540
01:50:40,920 --> 01:50:42,980
because those who have lived before thee

2541
01:50:43,000 --> 01:50:44,480
did not praise thee.

2542
01:50:45,000 --> 01:50:46,280
If a thing is difficult

2543
01:50:46,280 --> 01:50:47,880
to be accomplished by thyself,

2544
01:50:48,260 --> 01:50:50,520
do not think that it is impossible for man.

2545
01:50:50,960 --> 01:50:52,900
But if anything is possible for man

2546
01:50:52,900 --> 01:50:54,700
and conformable to his nature,

2547
01:50:55,080 --> 01:50:56,500
think that this can be attained

2548
01:50:56,500 --> 01:50:57,600
by thyself too.

2549
01:50:58,080 --> 01:50:59,660
In the gymnastic exercises

2550
01:50:59,660 --> 01:51:01,460
suppose that a man has torn thee

2551
01:51:01,460 --> 01:51:02,240
with his nails

2552
01:51:02,240 --> 01:51:04,160
and by dashing against thy head

2553
01:51:04,160 --> 01:51:05,260
has inflicted a wound.

2554
01:51:06,230 --> 01:51:07,790
Well, we neither show

2555
01:51:07,790 --> 01:51:09,390
any signs of vexation,

2556
01:51:09,630 --> 01:51:10,630
nor are we offended,

2557
01:51:11,210 --> 01:51:12,930
nor do we suspect him afterwards

2558
01:51:12,930 --> 01:51:14,250
as a treacherous fellow.

2559
01:51:15,000 --> 01:51:18,100
And yet we are on our guard against him,

2560
01:51:18,460 --> 01:51:19,980
not however as an enemy,

2561
01:51:20,280 --> 01:51:21,500
nor yet with suspicion.

2562
01:51:22,680 --> 01:51:24,520
But something like this,

2563
01:51:24,740 --> 01:51:26,120
let thy behavior be

2564
01:51:26,120 --> 01:51:27,860
in all the other parts of life.

2565
01:51:28,340 --> 01:51:30,080
Let us overlook many things

2566
01:51:30,080 --> 01:51:31,640
in those who are like

2567
01:51:31,640 --> 01:51:33,340
antagonists in the gymnasium.

2568
01:51:34,260 --> 01:51:36,560
For it is in our power, as I said,

2569
01:51:36,800 --> 01:51:37,820
to get out of the way

2570
01:51:37,820 --> 01:51:39,640
and to have no suspicion nor hatred.

2571
01:51:40,220 --> 01:51:42,640
If any man is able to convince me

2572
01:51:42,640 --> 01:51:44,380
and show me that I do not think

2573
01:51:44,380 --> 01:51:45,300
or act right,

2574
01:51:45,600 --> 01:51:46,940
I will gladly change,

2575
01:51:47,060 --> 01:51:48,380
for I seek the truth

2576
01:51:48,380 --> 01:51:50,580
by which no man was ever injured.

2577
01:51:54,760 --> 01:51:56,440
But he is injured who abides

2578
01:51:56,440 --> 01:51:58,000
in his error and ignorance.

2579
01:51:58,560 --> 01:51:59,740
I do my duty,

2580
01:52:00,060 --> 01:52:01,540
other things trouble me not,

2581
01:52:01,760 --> 01:52:03,740
for they are either things without life

2582
01:52:03,740 --> 01:52:05,260
or things without reason

2583
01:52:05,260 --> 01:52:07,020
or things that have rambled

2584
01:52:07,020 --> 01:52:08,480
and know not the way.

2585
01:52:09,020 --> 01:52:11,220
As to the animals which have no reason

2586
01:52:11,220 --> 01:52:13,380
and generally all things and objects,

2587
01:52:13,380 --> 01:52:16,020
do thou, since thou hast reason

2588
01:52:16,020 --> 01:52:17,000
and they have none,

2589
01:52:17,400 --> 01:52:18,420
make use of them

2590
01:52:18,420 --> 01:52:20,900
with an ingenuous and liberal spirit,

2591
01:52:21,220 --> 01:52:22,600
but towards human beings,

2592
01:52:22,900 --> 01:52:24,240
as they have reason,

2593
01:52:24,660 --> 01:52:26,320
behave in a social spirit.

2594
01:52:30,730 --> 01:52:32,150
Alexander the Macedonian

2595
01:52:32,150 --> 01:52:33,510
and his groom by death

2596
01:52:33,510 --> 01:52:35,210
were brought to the same state,

2597
01:52:35,650 --> 01:52:37,090
for either they were received

2598
01:52:37,090 --> 01:52:38,810
among the same seminal principles

2599
01:52:38,810 --> 01:52:39,690
of the universe,

2600
01:52:40,150 --> 01:52:41,910
or they were alike dispersed

2601
01:52:41,910 --> 01:52:42,790
among the atoms.

2602
01:52:43,430 --> 01:52:45,290
Consider how many things

2603
01:52:45,290 --> 01:52:47,230
in the same indivisible time

2604
01:52:47,230 --> 01:52:49,150
take place in each of us.

2605
01:52:50,890 --> 01:52:52,390
Things which concern the body

2606
01:52:52,390 --> 01:52:54,170
and things which concern the soul.

2607
01:52:57,210 --> 01:52:58,990
If any man should propose to thee

2608
01:52:58,990 --> 01:53:01,490
the question how the name Antoninus

2609
01:53:01,490 --> 01:53:02,090
is written,

2610
01:53:02,570 --> 01:53:03,810
wouldst thou with the straining

2611
01:53:03,810 --> 01:53:05,590
of the voice utter each letter?

2612
01:53:06,430 --> 01:53:08,390
What then, if they grow angry,

2613
01:53:08,830 --> 01:53:10,430
wilt thou be angry too?

2614
01:53:11,090 --> 01:53:13,250
Wilt thou not go on with composure

2615
01:53:13,250 --> 01:53:14,590
and number every letter?

2616
01:53:14,910 --> 01:53:17,190
Just so, then in this life

2617
01:53:17,190 --> 01:53:19,470
also remember that every duty

2618
01:53:19,470 --> 01:53:21,270
is made up of certain parts.

2619
01:53:22,070 --> 01:53:24,770
These it is thy duty to observe

2620
01:53:24,770 --> 01:53:26,530
and without being disturbed

2621
01:53:26,530 --> 01:53:28,190
or showing anger towards

2622
01:53:28,190 --> 01:53:29,970
those who are angry with thee

2623
01:53:29,970 --> 01:53:31,550
to go on thy way

2624
01:53:31,550 --> 01:53:34,250
and finish that which is set before thee.

2625
01:53:34,670 --> 01:53:37,230
How cruel it is not to allow men

2626
01:53:37,230 --> 01:53:38,650
to strive after the things

2627
01:53:38,650 --> 01:53:39,770
which appear to them

2628
01:53:39,770 --> 01:53:41,890
to be suitable to their nature

2629
01:53:41,890 --> 01:53:42,810
and profitable.

2630
01:53:45,790 --> 01:53:47,190
For they are certainly moved

2631
01:53:47,190 --> 01:53:48,850
towards things because they suppose

2632
01:53:48,850 --> 01:53:50,490
them to be suitable to their nature

2633
01:53:50,490 --> 01:53:52,170
and profitable to them.

2634
01:53:53,390 --> 01:53:55,390
But knit is not so.

2635
01:53:56,070 --> 01:53:56,930
Teach them then

2636
01:53:56,930 --> 01:53:58,670
and show them without being angry.

2637
01:53:59,510 --> 01:54:01,710
Death is a cessation of the impressions

2638
01:54:01,710 --> 01:54:02,650
through the senses

2639
01:54:02,650 --> 01:54:04,550
and of the pulling of the strings

2640
01:54:04,550 --> 01:54:06,090
which move the appetites

2641
01:54:06,090 --> 01:54:07,630
and of the discursive movements.

2642
01:54:08,370 --> 01:54:10,930
It is a shame for the soul to be first

2643
01:54:10,930 --> 01:54:13,090
to give way in this life

2644
01:54:13,090 --> 01:54:15,950
when thy body does not give way.

2645
01:54:18,860 --> 01:54:21,040
Take care that thou art not made

2646
01:54:21,040 --> 01:54:22,020
into a Caesar,

2647
01:54:22,640 --> 01:54:24,820
that thou art not died with this die,

2648
01:54:25,180 --> 01:54:26,500
for such things happen.

2649
01:54:26,880 --> 01:54:29,140
Keep thyself then simple,

2650
01:54:29,480 --> 01:54:32,740
good, pure, serious,

2651
01:54:34,750 --> 01:54:36,630
free from affectation.

2652
01:54:42,720 --> 01:54:44,740
You need to add some text for me to talk.

2653
01:54:45,320 --> 01:54:47,900
Remember his constancy in every act

2654
01:54:47,900 --> 01:54:49,820
which was conformable to reason

2655
01:54:49,820 --> 01:54:51,980
and his evenness in all things

2656
01:54:51,980 --> 01:54:53,260
and his piety

2657
01:54:53,260 --> 01:54:55,720
and the serenity of his countenance

2658
01:54:55,720 --> 01:54:56,800
and his sweetness

2659
01:54:57,300 --> 01:54:59,620
and his disregard of empty fame

2660
01:54:59,620 --> 01:55:02,400
and his efforts to understand things

2661
01:55:02,400 --> 01:55:04,940
and how he would never let anything pass

2662
01:55:04,940 --> 01:55:06,140
without having first

2663
01:55:06,140 --> 01:55:08,320
most carefully examined it

2664
01:55:08,320 --> 01:55:09,020
and clearly.

2665
01:55:09,260 --> 01:55:12,000
You need to add some text for me to talk.

2666
01:55:12,560 --> 01:55:13,540
Understood it

2667
01:55:13,540 --> 01:55:15,200
and how he bore with those

2668
01:55:15,200 --> 01:55:16,740
who blamed him unjustly

2669
01:55:16,740 --> 01:55:18,400
without blaming them in return,

2670
01:55:18,860 --> 01:55:20,540
how he did nothing in a hurry

2671
01:55:20,540 --> 01:55:22,820
and how he listened not to Calamnes

2672
01:55:22,820 --> 01:55:24,760
and how exact an examiner

2673
01:55:24,760 --> 01:55:26,660
of manners and actions he was.

2674
01:55:29,200 --> 01:55:31,740
And patient and how he was able

2675
01:55:31,740 --> 01:55:33,660
on account of his sparing diet

2676
01:55:33,660 --> 01:55:35,380
to hold out to the evening.

2677
01:55:39,270 --> 01:55:41,690
Opinions and the pleasure that he had

2678
01:55:41,690 --> 01:55:43,810
when any man showed him anything better

2679
01:55:43,840 --> 01:55:45,980
and how religious he was

2680
01:55:45,980 --> 01:55:47,040
without superstition.

2681
01:55:48,080 --> 01:55:50,120
Reverence the gods and help men.

2682
01:55:50,820 --> 01:55:52,140
Short is life.

2683
01:55:54,720 --> 01:55:56,480
Return to thy sober senses

2684
01:55:56,480 --> 01:55:58,320
and call thyself back.

2685
01:56:02,060 --> 01:56:04,560
I consist of a little body

2686
01:56:04,560 --> 01:56:05,540
and a soul.

2687
01:56:06,400 --> 01:56:08,520
Now to this little body

2688
01:56:08,520 --> 01:56:09,920
all things are indifferent

2689
01:56:09,920 --> 01:56:12,560
for it is not able to perceive differences.

2690
01:56:15,160 --> 01:56:17,100
But whatever things are

2691
01:56:17,100 --> 01:56:18,760
the works of its own activity

2692
01:56:18,760 --> 01:56:20,900
all these are in its power.

2693
01:56:22,010 --> 01:56:23,030
And of these however

2694
01:56:23,030 --> 01:56:24,390
only those which are done

2695
01:56:24,390 --> 01:56:25,750
with reference to the present

2696
01:56:25,750 --> 01:56:27,250
for as to the future

2697
01:56:27,250 --> 01:56:29,170
and the past activities of the mind

2698
01:56:29,170 --> 01:56:31,410
even these are for the present

2699
01:56:31,410 --> 01:56:32,090
indifferent.

2700
01:56:32,770 --> 01:56:34,830
Neither the labor which the hand does

2701
01:56:34,830 --> 01:56:36,010
nor that of the foot

2702
01:56:36,010 --> 01:56:37,530
is contrary to nature.

2703
01:56:37,910 --> 01:56:40,250
So long as the foot does the foot's work

2704
01:56:40,250 --> 01:56:41,970
and the hand the hands.

2705
01:56:43,260 --> 01:56:46,100
So then neither to a man as a man

2706
01:56:46,100 --> 01:56:46,960
is his labor.

2707
01:56:47,780 --> 01:56:48,820
Contrary to nature.

2708
01:56:49,720 --> 01:56:51,580
So long as it does the things of a man

2709
01:56:51,580 --> 01:56:53,560
but if the labor is not contrary

2710
01:56:53,560 --> 01:56:54,340
to his nature

2711
01:56:54,340 --> 01:56:56,530
neither is it an evil to him.

2712
01:57:02,050 --> 01:57:04,310
Dost thou not see how the handy craftsmen

2713
01:57:04,310 --> 01:57:05,310
accommodate themselves

2714
01:57:05,310 --> 01:57:06,790
up to a certain point to those

2715
01:57:06,790 --> 01:57:08,650
who are not skilled in their craft.

2716
01:57:09,410 --> 01:57:11,270
Nevertheless they cling to the reason

2717
01:57:11,270 --> 01:57:12,870
the principles of their art.

2718
01:57:13,490 --> 01:57:15,410
Is it not strange if the architect

2719
01:57:15,410 --> 01:57:17,210
and the physician shall have more respect

2720
01:57:17,210 --> 01:57:17,890
to the reason

2721
01:57:17,890 --> 01:57:19,810
the principles of their own arts

2722
01:57:19,810 --> 01:57:21,650
than man to his own reason

2723
01:57:22,980 --> 01:57:25,260
which is common to him and the gods.

2724
01:57:26,330 --> 01:57:28,470
Asia, Europe are corners of the universe

2725
01:57:28,470 --> 01:57:30,970
all the sea a drop in the universe

2726
01:57:30,970 --> 01:57:33,230
ethos a little clod of the universe

2727
01:57:33,230 --> 01:57:36,070
all the present time is a point in eternity.

2728
01:57:36,530 --> 01:57:39,330
All things are little changeable perishable

2729
01:57:39,910 --> 01:57:41,910
all things come from thence

2730
01:57:41,910 --> 01:57:43,710
from that universal ruling power

2731
01:57:43,730 --> 01:57:45,070
either directly proceeding

2732
01:57:45,070 --> 01:57:46,590
or by way of sequence.

2733
01:57:47,150 --> 01:57:49,290
And accordingly the lion's gaping jaws

2734
01:57:49,290 --> 01:57:50,970
and that which is poisonous

2735
01:57:50,970 --> 01:57:52,450
and every harmful thing

2736
01:57:52,450 --> 01:57:54,030
as a thorn as mud

2737
01:57:54,030 --> 01:57:56,490
are after products of the grand and beautiful.

2738
01:57:56,950 --> 01:57:58,270
Do not then imagine

2739
01:57:58,270 --> 01:58:00,050
that they are of another kind

2740
01:58:00,050 --> 01:58:02,010
from that which thou dost venerate

2741
01:58:02,010 --> 01:58:03,530
but form a just opinion

2742
01:58:03,530 --> 01:58:04,830
of the source of all.

2743
01:58:05,410 --> 01:58:07,390
He who has seen present things

2744
01:58:07,390 --> 01:58:08,410
has seen all

2745
01:58:08,410 --> 01:58:09,590
both everything

2746
01:58:09,590 --> 01:58:11,590
which has taken place from all eternity

2747
01:58:11,590 --> 01:58:12,590
and everything

2748
01:58:12,590 --> 01:58:14,870
which will be for time without end.

2749
01:58:15,670 --> 01:58:17,670
For all things are of one kin

2750
01:58:17,670 --> 01:58:18,730
and of one form.

2751
01:58:19,170 --> 01:58:20,790
Frequently consider the connection

2752
01:58:20,790 --> 01:58:22,270
of all things in the universe

2753
01:58:22,270 --> 01:58:23,850
and their relation to one another.

2754
01:58:24,350 --> 01:58:25,830
For in a manner all things

2755
01:58:25,830 --> 01:58:27,330
are implicated with one another

2756
01:58:27,330 --> 01:58:28,830
and all in this way

2757
01:58:28,830 --> 01:58:30,190
are friendly to one another.

2758
01:58:30,550 --> 01:58:32,830
For one thing comes in order after another

2759
01:58:32,830 --> 01:58:34,090
and this is by virtue

2760
01:58:34,090 --> 01:58:35,230
of the act of movement

2761
01:58:35,230 --> 01:58:36,770
and mutual conspiration

2762
01:58:36,770 --> 01:58:38,190
and the unity of thee.

2763
01:58:38,670 --> 01:58:40,350
Adapt thyself to the things

2764
01:58:40,350 --> 01:58:42,290
with which thy lot has been cast

2765
01:58:42,290 --> 01:58:43,930
and the man among whom

2766
01:58:43,930 --> 01:58:45,590
thou hast received thy portion.

2767
01:58:46,250 --> 01:58:48,970
Love them but do it truly, sincerely.

2768
01:58:51,070 --> 01:58:54,170
Every instrument, tool, vessel,

2769
01:58:55,220 --> 01:58:57,080
vessel, if it does that

2770
01:58:57,080 --> 01:58:59,520
for which it has been made, is well.

2771
01:59:00,410 --> 01:59:02,230
But in the things which are held

2772
01:59:02,230 --> 01:59:03,690
and together by nature

2773
01:59:03,690 --> 01:59:05,470
there is within

2774
01:59:06,480 --> 01:59:08,160
and there abides in them

2775
01:59:08,160 --> 01:59:10,160
the power which made them.

2776
01:59:10,820 --> 01:59:12,460
Wherefore the more is it fit

2777
01:59:12,460 --> 01:59:14,020
to reverence this power

2778
01:59:14,020 --> 01:59:16,060
and to think that

2779
01:59:16,060 --> 01:59:18,580
if thou dost live and act

2780
01:59:18,580 --> 01:59:19,840
according to its will,

2781
01:59:20,620 --> 01:59:22,040
everything in thee

2782
01:59:22,040 --> 01:59:24,320
is in conformity to intelligence.

2783
01:59:25,780 --> 01:59:27,240
You need to add some text

2784
01:59:27,240 --> 01:59:28,120
for me to talk.

2785
01:59:28,740 --> 01:59:29,680
Whatever of the things

2786
01:59:29,680 --> 01:59:31,540
which are not within thy power

2787
01:59:31,540 --> 01:59:33,920
thou shalt suppose to be good for thee

2788
01:59:33,920 --> 01:59:34,700
or evil.

2789
01:59:35,600 --> 01:59:37,600
It must of necessity be that.

2790
01:59:38,470 --> 01:59:40,350
If such a bad thing befall thee

2791
01:59:40,350 --> 01:59:42,290
or the loss of such a good thing

2792
01:59:42,290 --> 01:59:44,010
thou wilt blame the gods

2793
01:59:44,510 --> 01:59:45,970
and hate men too.

2794
01:59:46,490 --> 01:59:47,590
Those who are the cause

2795
01:59:47,590 --> 01:59:49,350
of the misfortune or the loss

2796
01:59:49,350 --> 01:59:51,070
or those who are suspected

2797
01:59:51,070 --> 01:59:53,470
of being likely to be the cause.

2798
01:59:53,970 --> 01:59:56,390
And indeed we do much injustice

2799
01:59:56,390 --> 01:59:58,110
because we make a difference

2800
01:59:58,110 --> 01:59:59,450
between these things.

2801
01:59:59,810 --> 02:00:01,430
And thus also in the universe

2802
02:00:01,430 --> 02:00:03,190
the things which belong to it

2803
02:00:03,190 --> 02:00:05,150
are in conformity to intelligence.

2804
02:00:06,640 --> 02:00:09,360
But if we judge only those things

2805
02:00:09,360 --> 02:00:10,400
which are in our power

2806
02:00:10,400 --> 02:00:11,760
to be good or bad

2807
02:00:12,710 --> 02:00:14,250
there remains no reason

2808
02:00:14,250 --> 02:00:16,230
either for finding fault with God

2809
02:00:16,230 --> 02:00:19,070
or standing in a hostile attitude to man.

2810
02:00:20,110 --> 02:00:21,550
We are all working together

2811
02:00:21,550 --> 02:00:22,470
to one end,

2812
02:00:22,630 --> 02:00:24,250
some with knowledge and design

2813
02:00:24,250 --> 02:00:25,850
and others without knowing

2814
02:00:25,850 --> 02:00:26,630
what they do.

2815
02:00:27,550 --> 02:00:29,730
As men also when they are asleep

2816
02:00:29,730 --> 02:00:32,770
of whom it is Heraclitus I think

2817
02:00:32,770 --> 02:00:33,950
who says that they are

2818
02:00:33,950 --> 02:00:35,250
laborers and cooperators

2819
02:00:35,250 --> 02:00:36,670
in the things which take place

2820
02:00:36,670 --> 02:00:37,470
in the universe.

2821
02:00:39,750 --> 02:00:40,890
But men cooperate

2822
02:00:40,890 --> 02:00:42,690
after different fashions

2823
02:00:42,690 --> 02:00:45,550
and even those cooperate abundantly.

2824
02:00:45,840 --> 02:00:48,140
Who find fault with what happens

2825
02:00:49,200 --> 02:00:51,080
and those who try to oppose it

2826
02:00:52,190 --> 02:00:53,490
and to hinder it.

2827
02:00:54,230 --> 02:00:55,610
For the universe had need

2828
02:00:56,320 --> 02:00:58,240
even of such man as these.

2829
02:00:58,880 --> 02:01:01,260
It remains then for thee to understand

2830
02:01:01,260 --> 02:01:03,140
among what kind of workman

2831
02:01:03,140 --> 02:01:04,520
thou places thyself.

2832
02:01:04,920 --> 02:01:06,840
For he who rules all things

2833
02:01:06,840 --> 02:01:08,900
will certainly make a right use of thee

2834
02:01:08,900 --> 02:01:10,540
and he will receive thee

2835
02:01:10,540 --> 02:01:12,180
among some part of the co.

2836
02:01:16,020 --> 02:01:17,720
But be not thou such a part

2837
02:01:17,720 --> 02:01:19,460
as the mean and ridiculous verse

2838
02:01:19,460 --> 02:01:20,200
in the play

2839
02:01:20,200 --> 02:01:22,060
which Chrysippus speaks of.

2840
02:01:23,100 --> 02:01:25,240
And does the sun undertake

2841
02:01:25,820 --> 02:01:27,460
to do the work of the rain?

2842
02:01:28,700 --> 02:01:30,360
Or Isculapius the work

2843
02:01:30,360 --> 02:01:32,220
of the fruit bearer, the earth?

2844
02:01:32,780 --> 02:01:34,420
And how is it with respect

2845
02:01:34,420 --> 02:01:35,400
to each of the stars?

2846
02:01:35,860 --> 02:01:36,840
Are they not different

2847
02:01:36,840 --> 02:01:38,120
and yet they work together

2848
02:01:38,120 --> 02:01:39,060
to the same end?

2849
02:01:39,600 --> 02:01:41,960
If the gods have determined about me

2850
02:01:41,960 --> 02:01:43,220
and about the things

2851
02:01:43,220 --> 02:01:44,760
which must happen to me

2852
02:01:44,760 --> 02:01:46,360
they have determined well.

2853
02:01:46,780 --> 02:01:48,180
For it is not easy even

2854
02:01:48,180 --> 02:01:49,180
to imagine a deity

2855
02:01:49,180 --> 02:01:50,260
without forethought.

2856
02:01:50,900 --> 02:01:52,440
And as to doing me harm

2857
02:01:52,440 --> 02:01:54,500
why should they have any desire?

2858
02:01:55,240 --> 02:01:57,300
For what advantage would result to them

2859
02:01:57,300 --> 02:01:59,300
from this or to the whole

2860
02:01:59,300 --> 02:02:01,180
which is the special object

2861
02:02:01,180 --> 02:02:02,180
of their providence?

2862
02:02:02,620 --> 02:02:04,420
But if they have not

2863
02:02:04,420 --> 02:02:06,120
determined about me individually

2864
02:02:06,120 --> 02:02:08,100
they have certainly determined

2865
02:02:08,100 --> 02:02:09,900
about the whole at least.

2866
02:02:10,460 --> 02:02:11,700
And the things which happen

2867
02:02:11,700 --> 02:02:12,760
by way of sequence

2868
02:02:12,760 --> 02:02:14,200
in this general arrangement

2869
02:02:14,200 --> 02:02:15,580
I ought to accept

2870
02:02:15,580 --> 02:02:17,620
with pleasure and to be.

2871
02:02:17,620 --> 02:02:19,440
You need to add some text

2872
02:02:19,440 --> 02:02:20,360
for me to talk.

2873
02:02:21,260 --> 02:02:22,240
But if they determine

2874
02:02:22,240 --> 02:02:22,980
about nothing

2875
02:02:22,980 --> 02:02:24,940
which it is wicked to believe

2876
02:02:24,940 --> 02:02:26,780
or if we do believe it

2877
02:02:26,780 --> 02:02:28,280
let us neither sacrifice

2878
02:02:28,280 --> 02:02:30,580
nor pray nor swear by them

2879
02:02:30,580 --> 02:02:32,240
nor do anything else

2880
02:02:32,240 --> 02:02:33,220
which we do

2881
02:02:33,220 --> 02:02:34,940
as if the gods were present

2882
02:02:34,940 --> 02:02:36,200
and lived with us.

2883
02:02:36,660 --> 02:02:38,480
But if however the gods determine

2884
02:02:38,480 --> 02:02:39,560
about none of the things

2885
02:02:39,560 --> 02:02:40,660
which concern us

2886
02:02:40,660 --> 02:02:42,120
I am able to determine

2887
02:02:42,120 --> 02:02:43,080
about myself

2888
02:02:43,080 --> 02:02:44,340
and I can.

2889
02:02:45,240 --> 02:02:46,260
Inquire about that

2890
02:02:46,260 --> 02:02:47,040
which is useful

2891
02:02:47,040 --> 02:02:49,000
and that is useful to every man

2892
02:02:49,000 --> 02:02:50,180
which is conformable

2893
02:02:50,180 --> 02:02:51,980
to his own constitution and nature.

2894
02:02:52,500 --> 02:02:54,220
But my nature is rational

2895
02:02:54,220 --> 02:02:55,080
and social

2896
02:02:55,080 --> 02:02:57,040
and my city and country

2897
02:02:57,040 --> 02:02:59,660
so far as I am Antoninus

2898
02:02:59,660 --> 02:03:00,480
is Rome.

2899
02:03:01,020 --> 02:03:02,540
But so far as I am a man

2900
02:03:03,740 --> 02:03:04,900
it is the world.

2901
02:03:08,770 --> 02:03:09,530
The things then

2902
02:03:09,530 --> 02:03:11,010
which are useful to these cities

2903
02:03:11,010 --> 02:03:12,710
are alone useful to me.

2904
02:03:13,460 --> 02:03:15,080
Whatever happens to every man

2905
02:03:15,080 --> 02:03:16,300
this is for the interest

2906
02:03:16,300 --> 02:03:17,260
of the universal

2907
02:03:17,260 --> 02:03:18,600
this might be sufficient.

2908
02:03:19,370 --> 02:03:20,590
But further thou wilt

2909
02:03:20,590 --> 02:03:21,850
observe this also

2910
02:03:21,850 --> 02:03:23,190
as a general truth.

2911
02:03:23,850 --> 02:03:25,250
If thou dost observe

2912
02:03:25,250 --> 02:03:27,070
that whatever is profitable

2913
02:03:27,070 --> 02:03:27,990
to any man

2914
02:03:27,990 --> 02:03:29,390
is profitable also

2915
02:03:29,390 --> 02:03:30,370
to other men.

2916
02:03:30,610 --> 02:03:31,930
But let the word profitable

2917
02:03:31,930 --> 02:03:32,930
be taken here

2918
02:03:32,930 --> 02:03:34,170
in the common sense

2919
02:03:34,170 --> 02:03:34,850
as said

2920
02:03:34,850 --> 02:03:36,510
of things of the middle kind

2921
02:03:36,510 --> 02:03:38,710
neither good nor bad.

2922
02:03:39,610 --> 02:03:41,510
As it happens to thee

2923
02:03:41,510 --> 02:03:42,670
in the amphitheatre

2924
02:03:42,670 --> 02:03:43,710
and such places

2925
02:03:43,710 --> 02:03:45,130
that the continual sight

2926
02:03:45,130 --> 02:03:46,250
of the same things

2927
02:03:46,250 --> 02:03:47,290
and the uniformity

2928
02:03:47,290 --> 02:03:48,930
make the spectacle wearisome

2929
02:03:48,930 --> 02:03:50,990
so it is in the whole of life

2930
02:03:50,990 --> 02:03:52,690
for all things above

2931
02:03:52,690 --> 02:03:54,290
below are the same.

2932
02:03:54,730 --> 02:03:55,850
How long then?

2933
02:03:56,250 --> 02:03:57,290
Think continually

2934
02:03:57,290 --> 02:03:59,010
that all kinds of men

2935
02:03:59,010 --> 02:04:00,850
and of all kinds of pursuits

2936
02:04:00,850 --> 02:04:02,770
and of all nations are dead

2937
02:04:03,290 --> 02:04:05,390
so that thy thoughts come down

2938
02:04:05,390 --> 02:04:07,230
even to Philistian

2939
02:04:08,430 --> 02:04:09,510
and Phoebus

2940
02:04:09,510 --> 02:04:11,150
and Oregonian.

2941
02:04:12,050 --> 02:04:13,530
Now turn thy thoughts

2942
02:04:13,530 --> 02:04:15,050
to the other kinds of men.

2943
02:04:15,590 --> 02:04:16,730
You need to add some text

2944
02:04:16,730 --> 02:04:17,790
for me to talk.

2945
02:04:17,790 --> 02:04:19,370
To that place then

2946
02:04:19,370 --> 02:04:20,450
we must remove

2947
02:04:20,450 --> 02:04:21,870
where there are so many

2948
02:04:21,870 --> 02:04:22,810
great orators

2949
02:04:22,810 --> 02:04:25,110
and so many noble philosophers

2950
02:04:25,890 --> 02:04:26,610
Heraclitus

2951
02:04:26,610 --> 02:04:27,310
Pythagoras

2952
02:04:28,090 --> 02:04:28,810
Socrates

2953
02:04:28,810 --> 02:04:30,250
so many heroes

2954
02:04:30,250 --> 02:04:31,330
of former days

2955
02:04:31,330 --> 02:04:32,910
and so many generals

2956
02:04:32,910 --> 02:04:33,830
after them

2957
02:04:33,830 --> 02:04:35,230
and tyrants

2958
02:04:35,230 --> 02:04:36,630
besides these

2959
02:04:36,630 --> 02:04:37,230
Eudoxus

2960
02:04:38,690 --> 02:04:39,410
Hipparchus

2961
02:04:40,470 --> 02:04:41,510
Confident

2962
02:04:41,510 --> 02:04:42,610
mockers even

2963
02:04:42,610 --> 02:04:43,610
of the perishable

2964
02:04:43,610 --> 02:04:45,170
and ephemeral life of man

2965
02:04:45,170 --> 02:04:46,230
as Manipus

2966
02:04:46,230 --> 02:04:48,030
and such as are like him.

2967
02:04:48,030 --> 02:04:49,530
As to all these

2968
02:04:49,530 --> 02:04:51,090
consider that they have long

2969
02:04:51,090 --> 02:04:51,950
been in the dust.

2970
02:04:52,710 --> 02:04:54,430
What harm then is this to them

2971
02:04:54,430 --> 02:04:55,830
and what to those

2972
02:04:55,830 --> 02:04:57,710
whose names are altogether unknown?

2973
02:04:59,170 --> 02:05:00,110
One thing here

2974
02:05:00,110 --> 02:05:01,410
is worth a great deal

2975
02:05:01,410 --> 02:05:02,850
to pass thy life

2976
02:05:02,850 --> 02:05:04,190
in truth and justice

2977
02:05:04,190 --> 02:05:06,050
with a benevolent disposition

2978
02:05:06,050 --> 02:05:07,190
