02:13:31,810 --> 02:13:33,470
But the soul itself,

3272
02:13:33,930 --> 02:13:35,030
that which is subject

3273
02:13:35,030 --> 02:13:35,710
to fear,

3274
02:13:35,890 --> 02:13:36,390
to pain,

3275
02:13:36,790 --> 02:13:37,770
which has completely

3276
02:13:37,770 --> 02:13:38,990
the power of forming

3277
02:13:38,990 --> 02:13:40,730
an opinion about these things,

3278
02:13:41,010 --> 02:13:42,150
will suffer nothing,

3279
02:13:42,670 --> 02:13:44,210
for it will never deviate

3280
02:13:44,210 --> 02:13:45,310
into such a judgment.

3281
02:13:45,950 --> 02:13:47,090
The leading principle

3282
02:13:47,090 --> 02:13:47,950
in itself

3283
02:13:47,950 --> 02:13:49,130
wants nothing,

3284
02:13:49,770 --> 02:13:51,030
unless it makes a want

3285
02:13:51,030 --> 02:13:51,910
for itself,

3286
02:13:51,910 --> 02:13:53,210
and therefore,

3287
02:13:53,530 --> 02:13:54,530
it is both free

3288
02:13:54,530 --> 02:13:55,630
from perturbation,

3289
02:13:55,890 --> 02:13:57,030
and unimpeded,

3290
02:13:57,210 --> 02:13:58,430
if it does not disturb

3291
02:13:58,430 --> 02:13:59,610
and impede itself.

3292
02:14:04,660 --> 02:14:06,280
What then art thou doing here,

3293
02:14:06,440 --> 02:14:07,320
O imagination?

3294
02:14:07,960 --> 02:14:08,740
Go away,

3295
02:14:09,000 --> 02:14:10,580
I entreat thee by the gods,

3296
02:14:10,780 --> 02:14:11,920
as thou didst come,

3297
02:14:12,120 --> 02:14:13,560
for I want thee not.

3298
02:14:18,150 --> 02:14:20,210
Is any man afraid of change?

3299
02:14:20,610 --> 02:14:21,090
Why?

3300
02:14:21,370 --> 02:14:22,450
What can take place

3301
02:14:22,450 --> 02:14:23,330
without change?

3302
02:14:23,870 --> 02:14:25,250
What then is more pleasing,

3303
02:14:25,490 --> 02:14:26,230
or more suitable

3304
02:14:26,230 --> 02:14:27,690
to the universal nature?

3305
02:14:28,510 --> 02:14:30,130
And canst thou take a bath,

3306
02:14:30,130 --> 02:14:31,030
unless the wood

3307
02:14:31,030 --> 02:14:32,330
undergoes a change?

3308
02:14:33,510 --> 02:14:35,050
And canst thou be nourished,

3309
02:14:35,310 --> 02:14:36,170
unless the food

3310
02:14:36,170 --> 02:14:37,590
undergoes an inchange?

3311
02:14:42,420 --> 02:14:44,160
Through the universal substance,

3312
02:14:44,500 --> 02:14:46,200
as through a furious torrent,

3313
02:14:46,560 --> 02:14:47,840
all bodies are carried,

3314
02:14:48,240 --> 02:14:49,320
being by their nature

3315
02:14:49,320 --> 02:14:50,360
united with,

3316
02:14:50,640 --> 02:14:51,880
and cooperating with,

3317
02:14:52,140 --> 02:14:52,760
the whole,

3318
02:14:53,200 --> 02:14:54,460
as the parts of our body

3319
02:14:54,460 --> 02:14:55,320
with one another.

3320
02:14:59,420 --> 02:15:00,700
And let the same thought

3321
02:15:00,700 --> 02:15:01,420
occur to thee

3322
02:15:01,420 --> 02:15:02,080
with reference

3323
02:15:02,080 --> 02:15:03,500
to every man and thing.

3324
02:15:03,960 --> 02:15:06,040
One thing only troubles me,

3325
02:15:06,340 --> 02:15:07,500
lest I should do something

3326
02:15:07,500 --> 02:15:09,220
which the constitution of man

3327
02:15:09,220 --> 02:15:10,140
does not allow,

3328
02:15:10,540 --> 02:15:11,380
or in the way which

3329
02:15:11,380 --> 02:15:12,420
it does not allow,

3330
02:15:12,580 --> 02:15:14,260
or what it does not allow now,

3331
02:15:14,780 --> 02:15:16,300
near is thy forgetfulness

3332
02:15:16,300 --> 02:15:17,240
of all things,

3333
02:15:17,500 --> 02:15:18,900
and near the forgetfulness

3334
02:15:18,900 --> 02:15:20,040
of thee by all.

3335
02:15:20,640 --> 02:15:22,160
It is peculiar to man

3336
02:15:22,160 --> 02:15:23,380
to love even those

3337
02:15:23,380 --> 02:15:24,200
who do wrong.

3338
02:15:24,720 --> 02:15:25,760
And this happens,

3339
02:15:26,240 --> 02:15:27,680
if, when they do wrong,

3340
02:15:27,980 --> 02:15:28,980
it occurs to thee

3341
02:15:28,980 --> 02:15:30,460
that they are kinsmen,

3342
02:15:30,840 --> 02:15:32,180
and that they do wrong

3343
02:15:32,180 --> 02:15:32,900
through ignorance

3344
02:15:32,900 --> 02:15:34,500
and unintentionally,

3345
02:15:34,540 --> 02:15:35,540
and that soon

3346
02:15:35,540 --> 02:15:36,920
both of you will die.

3347
02:15:40,490 --> 02:15:42,570
Wrongdoer has done thee no harm,

3348
02:15:42,770 --> 02:15:43,870
for he has not made

3349
02:15:43,870 --> 02:15:45,030
thy ruling faculty

3350
02:15:45,030 --> 02:15:46,470
worse than it was before.

3351
02:15:46,770 --> 02:15:48,070
The universal nature

3352
02:15:48,070 --> 02:15:49,950
out of the universal substance,

3353
02:15:50,210 --> 02:15:51,410
as if it were wax,

3354
02:15:51,790 --> 02:15:53,410
now molds a horse,

3355
02:15:53,830 --> 02:15:55,570
and when it has broken this up,

3356
02:15:55,950 --> 02:15:57,950
it uses the material for a tree,

3357
02:15:58,190 --> 02:15:59,570
then for a man,

3358
02:15:59,990 --> 02:16:01,550
then for something else,

3359
02:16:01,750 --> 02:16:03,050
and each of these things

3360
02:16:03,050 --> 02:16:05,370
subsists for a very short time.

3361
02:16:05,630 --> 02:16:07,050
But it is no hardship

3362
02:16:07,050 --> 02:16:08,670
for the vessel to be broken up,

3363
02:16:08,870 --> 02:16:09,930
just as there was none

3364
02:16:09,930 --> 02:16:11,470
in its being fastened together.

3365
02:16:12,010 --> 02:16:13,030
A scowling look

3366
02:16:13,030 --> 02:16:14,570
is altogether unnatural,

3367
02:16:14,930 --> 02:16:16,150
when it is often assumed

3368
02:16:16,150 --> 02:16:17,290
the result is that

3369
02:16:17,290 --> 02:16:18,770
all comeliness dies,

3370
02:16:18,970 --> 02:16:20,430
and at last

3371
02:16:20,430 --> 02:16:22,250
is so completely extinguished

3372
02:16:22,250 --> 02:16:23,690
that it cannot be again

3373
02:16:23,690 --> 02:16:24,650
lighted up at all.

3374
02:16:24,810 --> 02:16:25,970
Try to conclude,

3375
02:16:26,310 --> 02:16:27,790
from this very fact,

3376
02:16:28,170 --> 02:16:30,110
that it is contrary to reason.

3377
02:16:30,890 --> 02:16:31,610
For if,

3378
02:16:31,890 --> 02:16:32,810
even the perception

3379
02:16:32,810 --> 02:16:34,350
of doing wrong shall depart,

3380
02:16:34,930 --> 02:16:36,070
what reason is there

3381
02:16:36,070 --> 02:16:37,290
for living any longer?

3382
02:16:37,870 --> 02:16:39,610
Nature which governs the whole

3383
02:16:39,610 --> 02:16:41,510
will soon change all things

3384
02:16:41,510 --> 02:16:42,490
which thou seest,

3385
02:16:42,830 --> 02:16:43,950
and out of their substance

3386
02:16:43,950 --> 02:16:45,130
will make other things,

3387
02:16:45,390 --> 02:16:46,770
and again other things

3388
02:16:46,770 --> 02:16:48,090
from the substance of them.

3389
02:16:48,670 --> 02:16:50,390
In, when a man has done

3390
02:16:50,390 --> 02:16:51,190
thee any wrong,

3391
02:16:51,630 --> 02:16:52,570
immediately consider

3392
02:16:52,570 --> 02:16:53,430
with what opinion

3393
02:16:53,430 --> 02:16:54,430
about good or evil

3394
02:16:54,430 --> 02:16:55,570
he has done wrong.

3395
02:16:56,130 --> 02:16:57,470
For when thou hast seen this,

3396
02:16:57,710 --> 02:16:58,670
thou wilt pity him,

3397
02:16:58,810 --> 02:16:59,990
and wilt neither wonder

3398
02:16:59,990 --> 02:17:01,070
nor be angry.

3399
02:17:01,330 --> 02:17:02,710
For either thou thyself

3400
02:17:02,710 --> 02:17:03,730
thinkest the same thing

3401
02:17:03,730 --> 02:17:04,390
to be good,

3402
02:17:04,570 --> 02:17:05,430
that he does,

3403
02:17:05,830 --> 02:17:06,610
or another thing

3404
02:17:06,610 --> 02:17:07,650
of the same kind,

3405
02:17:07,970 --> 02:17:09,270
it is thy duty then

3406
02:17:09,270 --> 02:17:10,250
to pardon him.

3407
02:17:13,950 --> 02:17:15,030
Think not so much

3408
02:17:15,030 --> 02:17:16,250
of what thou hast not

3409
02:17:16,250 --> 02:17:17,550
as of what thou hast,

3410
02:17:17,910 --> 02:17:18,670
but of the things

3411
02:17:18,670 --> 02:17:20,370
which thou hast select the best,

3412
02:17:20,650 --> 02:17:21,330
and then reflect

3413
02:17:21,330 --> 02:17:22,090
how eagerly

3414
02:17:22,090 --> 02:17:23,050
they would have been sought.

3415
02:17:23,940 --> 02:17:25,280
If thou hast them not,

3416
02:17:25,680 --> 02:17:27,240
at the same time, however,

3417
02:17:27,680 --> 02:17:29,740
take care that thou dost not,

3418
02:17:29,880 --> 02:17:31,660
through being so pleased with them,

3419
02:17:31,940 --> 02:17:32,860
accustom thyself

3420
02:17:32,860 --> 02:17:34,280
to overvalue them,

3421
02:17:34,420 --> 02:17:35,620
so as to be disturbed,

3422
02:17:35,860 --> 02:17:36,460
if ever,

3423
02:17:36,820 --> 02:17:38,140
retire into thyself.

3424
02:17:38,380 --> 02:17:39,540
The rational principle

3425
02:17:39,540 --> 02:17:41,220
which rules has this nature,

3426
02:17:41,220 --> 02:17:42,960
that it is content with itself

3427
02:17:42,960 --> 02:17:44,420
when it does what is just,

3428
02:17:44,720 --> 02:17:46,540
and so secures tranquility.

3429
02:17:47,160 --> 02:17:48,540
Wipe out the imagination.

3430
02:17:49,260 --> 02:17:50,840
Stop the pulling of the strings.

3431
02:17:51,260 --> 02:17:52,900
Confine thyself to the present.

3432
02:17:53,620 --> 02:17:54,440
Understand well

3433
02:17:54,440 --> 02:17:55,800
what happens either to thee

3434
02:17:55,800 --> 02:17:56,740
or to another.

3435
02:17:57,320 --> 02:17:58,540
Divide and distribute

3436
02:17:58,540 --> 02:18:00,460
every object into the causal,

3437
02:18:00,800 --> 02:18:01,380
informal,

3438
02:18:01,840 --> 02:18:02,660
and the material.

3439
02:18:05,550 --> 02:18:06,570
Direct thy attention

3440
02:18:06,570 --> 02:18:07,350
to what is said.

3441
02:18:07,790 --> 02:18:08,710
Let thy understanding

3442
02:18:08,710 --> 02:18:09,870
enter into the things

3443
02:18:09,870 --> 02:18:10,530
that are doing,

3444
02:18:10,670 --> 02:18:12,070
and the things which do them.

3445
02:18:16,150 --> 02:18:18,130
Adorn thyself with simplicity

3446
02:18:18,130 --> 02:18:19,130
and modesty

3447
02:18:19,130 --> 02:18:20,170
and with indifference

3448
02:18:20,170 --> 02:18:21,650
towards the things which lie

3449
02:18:21,650 --> 02:18:23,330
between virtue and vice.

3450
02:18:24,070 --> 02:18:25,650
Love mankind.

3451
02:18:29,840 --> 02:18:30,560
About pain,

3452
02:18:30,920 --> 02:18:32,300
the pain which is intolerable

3453
02:18:32,300 --> 02:18:33,220
carries us off.

3454
02:18:33,760 --> 02:18:34,800
But that which lasts

3455
02:18:34,800 --> 02:18:35,960
a long time

3456
02:18:35,960 --> 02:18:37,100
is tolerable.

3457
02:18:40,790 --> 02:18:41,470
But the parts

3458
02:18:41,470 --> 02:18:43,010
which are harmed by pain,

3459
02:18:43,190 --> 02:18:43,710
let them,

3460
02:18:43,710 --> 02:18:44,550
if they can,

3461
02:18:44,850 --> 02:18:46,770
give their opinion about it.

3462
02:18:47,370 --> 02:18:48,130
About fame,

3463
02:18:48,390 --> 02:18:49,250
look at the minds

3464
02:18:49,250 --> 02:18:50,670
of those who seek fame.

3465
02:18:50,670 --> 02:18:52,210
Observe what they are,

3466
02:18:52,330 --> 02:18:54,090
and what kind of things they avoid,

3467
02:18:54,330 --> 02:18:56,150
and what kind of things they pursue.

3468
02:18:56,630 --> 02:18:57,730
And consider that,

3469
02:18:57,970 --> 02:18:59,730
as the heaps of sand piled

3470
02:18:59,730 --> 02:19:00,590
on one another

3471
02:19:00,590 --> 02:19:01,990
hide the former sands,

3472
02:19:02,330 --> 02:19:03,550
so in life the events

3473
02:19:03,550 --> 02:19:04,530
which go before

3474
02:19:04,530 --> 02:19:05,630
are soon covered

3475
02:19:05,630 --> 02:19:07,150
by those which come after.

3476
02:19:07,780 --> 02:19:08,480
From Plato,

3477
02:19:08,800 --> 02:19:09,680
the man who has

3478
02:19:09,680 --> 02:19:10,720
an elevated mind

3479
02:19:10,720 --> 02:19:12,200
and takes a view of all time

3480
02:19:12,200 --> 02:19:13,160
and of all substance,

3481
02:19:13,700 --> 02:19:14,980
dost thou suppose it possible

3482
02:19:14,980 --> 02:19:15,800
for him to think

3483
02:19:15,800 --> 02:19:16,480
that human life

3484
02:19:16,480 --> 02:19:17,320
is anything great?

3485
02:19:17,480 --> 02:19:18,760
It is not possible,

3486
02:19:18,900 --> 02:19:19,500
he said.

3487
02:19:19,500 --> 02:19:21,400
Such a man then will think

3488
02:19:21,400 --> 02:19:23,220
that death also is no evil.

3489
02:19:26,730 --> 02:19:27,750
Certainly not.

3490
02:19:30,430 --> 02:19:31,710
From Antisthenes

3491
02:19:31,710 --> 02:19:33,070
it is royal to do good

3492
02:19:33,070 --> 02:19:34,050
and to be abused.

3493
02:19:34,530 --> 02:19:35,630
It is a base thing

3494
02:19:35,630 --> 02:19:36,630
for the countenance

3495
02:19:36,630 --> 02:19:37,590
to be obedient

3496
02:19:37,590 --> 02:19:38,770
and to regulate

3497
02:19:38,770 --> 02:19:39,950
and compose itself

3498
02:19:39,950 --> 02:19:41,390
as the mind commands,

3499
02:19:41,910 --> 02:19:42,730
and for the mind

3500
02:19:42,730 --> 02:19:43,850
not to be regulated

3501
02:19:43,850 --> 02:19:45,730
and composed by itself.

3502
02:19:46,330 --> 02:19:47,190
It is not right

3503
02:19:47,190 --> 02:19:48,850
to vex ourselves at things,

3504
02:19:49,210 --> 02:19:50,890
for they care not about it.

3505
02:19:51,210 --> 02:19:52,470
To the immortal gods

3506
02:19:52,470 --> 02:19:53,790
and us give joy.

3507
02:19:57,370 --> 02:19:58,850
For the good is with me,

3508
02:19:58,890 --> 02:19:59,510
and the just.

3509
02:20:00,740 --> 02:20:01,640
No joining others

3510
02:20:01,640 --> 02:20:02,400
in their wailing,

3511
02:20:02,700 --> 02:20:03,960
no violent emotion.

3512
02:20:04,810 --> 02:20:05,530
From Plato,

3513
02:20:05,930 --> 02:20:07,110
but I would make this man

3514
02:20:07,110 --> 02:20:08,250
a sufficient answer,

3515
02:20:08,910 --> 02:20:09,770
which is this.

3516
02:20:10,370 --> 02:20:11,850
Thou sayest not well,

3517
02:20:12,130 --> 02:20:13,290
if thou thinkest

3518
02:20:13,290 --> 02:20:14,010
that a man

3519
02:20:14,010 --> 02:20:14,610
who is good

3520
02:20:14,610 --> 02:20:15,990
for anything at all

3521
02:20:15,990 --> 02:20:16,850
ought to compute

3522
02:20:16,850 --> 02:20:17,930
the hazard of life

3523
02:20:17,930 --> 02:20:18,590
or death,

3524
02:20:18,970 --> 02:20:19,930
and should not rather

3525
02:20:19,930 --> 02:20:20,670
look to this

3526
02:20:20,670 --> 02:20:21,870
only in all that.

3527
02:20:22,310 --> 02:20:23,090
He does,

3528
02:20:23,590 --> 02:20:24,510
whether he is doing

3529
02:20:24,510 --> 02:20:26,150
what is just or unjust,

3530
02:20:26,590 --> 02:20:27,730
and the works of a good

3531
02:20:27,730 --> 02:20:29,230
or a bad man.

3532
02:20:30,060 --> 02:20:31,240
For thus it is,

3533
02:20:31,480 --> 02:20:32,340
man of Athens,

3534
02:20:32,720 --> 02:20:33,340
in truth,

3535
02:20:33,840 --> 02:20:34,560
wherever a man

3536
02:20:34,560 --> 02:20:35,560
has placed himself

3537
02:20:35,560 --> 02:20:37,380
thinking at the best place for him,

3538
02:20:37,580 --> 02:20:38,580
or has been placed

3539
02:20:38,580 --> 02:20:39,320
by a commander.

3540
02:20:42,220 --> 02:20:43,160
There, in my opinion,

3541
02:20:43,280 --> 02:20:44,080
he ought to stay

3542
02:20:44,080 --> 02:20:45,360
and to abide the hazard,

3543
02:20:47,580 --> 02:20:48,320
taking nothing

3544
02:20:48,320 --> 02:20:49,180
into the reckoning,

3545
02:20:49,360 --> 02:20:50,020
either death

3546
02:20:50,020 --> 02:20:51,020
or anything else

3547
02:20:51,020 --> 02:20:51,920
before the baseness

3548
02:20:51,920 --> 02:20:53,080
of deserting his post.

3549
02:20:54,400 --> 02:20:55,760
You need to add some text

3550
02:20:55,760 --> 02:20:56,620
for me to talk.

3551
02:20:57,690 --> 02:20:58,170
N.

3552
02:20:59,260 --> 02:21:00,720
But, my good friend,

3553
02:21:01,280 --> 02:21:02,500
reflect whether that

3554
02:21:02,500 --> 02:21:03,820
which is noble and good

3555
02:21:03,820 --> 02:21:05,220
is not something different

3556
02:21:05,220 --> 02:21:06,860
from saving and being saved,

3557
02:21:07,200 --> 02:21:08,180
for as to a man

3558
02:21:08,180 --> 02:21:09,780
living such or such a time,

3559
02:21:10,100 --> 02:21:10,920
at least one

3560
02:21:10,920 --> 02:21:12,220
who is really a man,

3561
02:21:12,640 --> 02:21:14,460
consider if this is not a thing

3562
02:21:14,460 --> 02:21:15,280
to be dismissed

3563
02:21:15,280 --> 02:21:16,180
from the thoughts,

3564
02:21:16,580 --> 02:21:17,400
and there must be

3565
02:21:17,400 --> 02:21:18,480
no love of life.

3566
02:21:19,100 --> 02:21:20,420
But as to these matters

3567
02:21:20,420 --> 02:21:22,420
a man must entrust.

3568
02:21:23,020 --> 02:21:24,400
Damn to the deity,

3569
02:21:24,920 --> 02:21:25,660
and believe

3570
02:21:25,660 --> 02:21:26,780
what the women say,

3571
02:21:27,180 --> 02:21:28,000
that no man

3572
02:21:28,000 --> 02:21:29,320
can escape his destiny.

3573
02:21:29,780 --> 02:21:30,700
The next inquiry

3574
02:21:30,700 --> 02:21:32,360
being how he may best live

3575
02:21:32,360 --> 02:21:34,020
the time that he has to live.

3576
02:21:34,280 --> 02:21:35,460
Look round at the courses

3577
02:21:35,460 --> 02:21:36,280
of the stars,

3578
02:21:36,640 --> 02:21:37,360
as if thou wert

3579
02:21:37,360 --> 02:21:38,620
going along with them,

3580
02:21:38,920 --> 02:21:40,060
and constantly consider

3581
02:21:40,060 --> 02:21:41,440
the changes of the elements

3582
02:21:41,440 --> 02:21:42,380
into one another,

3583
02:21:42,760 --> 02:21:43,640
for such thoughts

3584
02:21:43,640 --> 02:21:44,940
purge away the filth

3585
02:21:44,940 --> 02:21:45,880
of the Terran life.

3586
02:21:46,300 --> 02:21:47,900
You need to add some text

3587
02:21:47,900 --> 02:21:48,800
for me to talk.

3588
02:21:49,240 --> 02:21:51,160
This is a fine saying of Plato,

3589
02:21:51,540 --> 02:21:52,980
that he who is discoursing

3590
02:21:52,980 --> 02:21:53,780
about men

3591
02:21:53,780 --> 02:21:54,960
should look also

3592
02:21:54,960 --> 02:21:56,240
at earthly things,

3593
02:21:56,500 --> 02:21:57,760
as if he viewed them

3594
02:21:57,760 --> 02:21:59,260
from some higher place,

3595
02:21:59,260 --> 02:22:00,860
should look at them

3596
02:22:00,860 --> 02:22:02,080
in their assemblies,

3597
02:22:02,420 --> 02:22:02,980
armies,

3598
02:22:03,340 --> 02:22:04,540
agricultural labors,

3599
02:22:04,840 --> 02:22:05,360
marriages,

3600
02:22:05,760 --> 02:22:06,160
treaties,

3601
02:22:06,400 --> 02:22:07,060
births,

3602
02:22:07,200 --> 02:22:07,600
deaths,

3603
02:22:08,080 --> 02:22:09,780
noise of the courts of justice,

3604
02:22:10,160 --> 02:22:10,900
desert places,

3605
02:22:11,240 --> 02:22:13,020
various nations of barbarians,

3606
02:22:13,340 --> 02:22:14,060
feasts,

3607
02:22:14,480 --> 02:22:15,320
lamentations,

3608
02:22:15,700 --> 02:22:16,120
markets,

3609
02:22:16,580 --> 02:22:17,880
a mixture of all things,

3610
02:22:18,020 --> 02:22:19,320
and an orderly combination

3611
02:22:19,320 --> 02:22:20,240
of contraries.

3612
02:22:20,500 --> 02:22:21,800
Consider the past,

3613
02:22:21,960 --> 02:22:22,900
such great changes

3614
02:22:22,900 --> 02:22:24,400
of political supremacies,

3615
02:22:24,620 --> 02:22:25,860
thou mayst foresee also

3616
02:22:25,860 --> 02:22:27,320
the things which will be,

3617
02:22:27,580 --> 02:22:28,940
for they will certainly be

3618
02:22:28,940 --> 02:22:29,940
of like form,

3619
02:22:30,220 --> 02:22:31,440
and it is not possible

3620
02:22:31,440 --> 02:22:32,700
that they should deviate

3621
02:22:32,700 --> 02:22:34,120
from the order of the things

3622
02:22:34,120 --> 02:22:35,420
which take place now.

3623
02:22:36,490 --> 02:22:37,030
Accordingly,

3624
02:22:37,050 --> 02:22:38,950
to have contemplated human life

3625
02:22:38,950 --> 02:22:40,150
for forty years

3626
02:22:40,150 --> 02:22:41,770
is the same as to have.

3627
02:22:42,490 --> 02:22:44,110
For what more wilt thou see,

3628
02:22:44,450 --> 02:22:45,370
that which is grown

3629
02:22:45,370 --> 02:22:46,810
from the earth to the earth,

3630
02:22:47,290 --> 02:22:48,530
but that which is sprung

3631
02:22:48,530 --> 02:22:49,750
from heavenly seed,

3632
02:22:50,590 --> 02:22:51,910
back to the heavenly realms

3633
02:22:51,910 --> 02:22:52,550
returns.

3634
02:22:53,760 --> 02:22:54,920
This is either

3635
02:22:54,920 --> 02:22:55,740
a dissolution

3636
02:22:55,740 --> 02:22:57,080
of the mutual involution

3637
02:22:57,080 --> 02:22:57,800
of the atoms,

3638
02:22:58,400 --> 02:23:00,120
or a similar indispersion

3639
02:23:00,120 --> 02:23:01,680
of the unsentient elements,

3640
02:23:02,800 --> 02:23:04,080
with food and drinks

3641
02:23:04,080 --> 02:23:05,360
and cunning magic arts

3642
02:23:05,360 --> 02:23:06,580
turning the channel's course

3643
02:23:06,580 --> 02:23:07,820
to escape from death.

3644
02:23:12,480 --> 02:23:14,180
Another may be more expert

3645
02:23:14,180 --> 02:23:15,380
in casting his opponent,

3646
02:23:15,680 --> 02:23:16,940
but he is not more social,

3647
02:23:17,220 --> 02:23:18,140
nor more modest,

3648
02:23:18,500 --> 02:23:19,480
nor better disciplined

3649
02:23:19,480 --> 02:23:21,140
to meet all that happens,

3650
02:23:21,420 --> 02:23:22,820
nor more considerate with.

3651
02:23:23,300 --> 02:23:24,340
Where any work

3652
02:23:24,340 --> 02:23:25,980
can be done conformably

3653
02:23:25,980 --> 02:23:27,500
to the reason which is common

3654
02:23:27,500 --> 02:23:28,880
to gods and men,

3655
02:23:29,500 --> 02:23:31,200
there we have nothing to fear.

3656
02:23:31,960 --> 02:23:33,280
For where we are able

3657
02:23:33,280 --> 02:23:34,120
to get profit

3658
02:23:34,120 --> 02:23:35,560
by means of the activity

3659
02:23:35,560 --> 02:23:36,620
which is successful

3660
02:23:36,620 --> 02:23:37,860
and proceeds according

3661
02:23:37,860 --> 02:23:39,060
to our constitution,

3662
02:23:39,720 --> 02:23:40,440
there no harm

3663
02:23:40,440 --> 02:23:41,620
is to be suspected.

3664
02:23:43,510 --> 02:23:45,470
Everywhere and at all times

3665
02:23:45,470 --> 02:23:47,030
it is in thy power

3666
02:23:47,030 --> 02:23:49,150
piously to acquiesce

3667
02:23:49,150 --> 02:23:50,430
in thy present condition,

3668
02:23:50,930 --> 02:23:52,110
and to behave justly

3669
02:23:52,110 --> 02:23:53,530
to those who are about thee,

3670
02:23:53,870 --> 02:23:55,650
and to exert thy skill

3671
02:23:55,650 --> 02:23:57,170
upon thy present thoughts,

3672
02:23:57,410 --> 02:23:59,130
that nothing shall steal into them

3673
02:23:59,130 --> 02:24:00,570
without being well examined.

3674
02:24:01,250 --> 02:24:02,750
Do not look around thee

3675
02:24:02,750 --> 02:24:04,030
to discover other men's

3676
02:24:04,030 --> 02:24:04,890
ruling principles,

3677
02:24:05,310 --> 02:24:06,630
but look straight to this,

3678
02:24:06,990 --> 02:24:08,530
to what nature leads thee,

3679
02:24:08,950 --> 02:24:10,530
both the universal nature

3680
02:24:10,530 --> 02:24:11,530
through the things

3681
02:24:11,530 --> 02:24:12,530
which happen to thee,

3682
02:24:12,870 --> 02:24:14,130
and thy own nature

3683
02:24:14,130 --> 02:24:15,250
through the acts

3684
02:24:15,250 --> 02:24:16,790
which must be done by thee.

3685
02:24:17,090 --> 02:24:18,630
But every being ought to do

3686
02:24:18,630 --> 02:24:19,750
that which is according

3687
02:24:19,750 --> 02:24:20,930
to its constitution,

3688
02:24:21,310 --> 02:24:22,450
and all other things

3689
02:24:22,450 --> 02:24:23,570
have been constituted

3690
02:24:23,570 --> 02:24:25,350
for the sake of rational beings,

3691
02:24:25,830 --> 02:24:27,870
just as among irrational things,

3692
02:24:28,230 --> 02:24:28,910
the inferior

3693
02:24:28,910 --> 02:24:30,430
for the sake of the superior.

3694
02:24:31,290 --> 02:24:32,450
But the rational,

3695
02:24:32,450 --> 02:24:33,970
for the sake of one another.

3696
02:24:35,010 --> 02:24:36,490
You need to add some text

3697
02:24:36,490 --> 02:24:37,350
for me to talk.

3698
02:24:38,280 --> 02:24:39,640
And the second is not to yield

3699
02:24:39,640 --> 02:24:41,300
to the persuasions of the body,

3700
02:24:41,940 --> 02:24:43,500
for it is the peculiar office

3701
02:24:43,500 --> 02:24:44,360
of the rational

3702
02:24:44,360 --> 02:24:45,620
and intelligent motion

3703
02:24:45,620 --> 02:24:47,360
to circumscribe itself,

3704
02:24:47,900 --> 02:24:49,440
and never to be overpowered,

3705
02:24:50,650 --> 02:24:51,670
either by the motion

3706
02:24:51,670 --> 02:24:52,530
of the senses

3707
02:24:52,530 --> 02:24:53,890
or of the appetites,

3708
02:24:54,510 --> 02:24:55,910
for both are animal.

3709
02:24:57,300 --> 02:24:58,540
But the intelligent motion

3710
02:24:58,540 --> 02:24:59,760
claims superiority.

3711
02:25:00,740 --> 02:25:02,120
The prime principle then

3712
02:25:02,120 --> 02:25:03,480
in man's constitution

3713
02:25:03,800 --> 02:25:05,140
is the in-social,

3714
02:25:05,970 --> 02:25:07,250
and with good reason,

3715
02:25:08,080 --> 02:25:09,280
for it is formed by nature

3716
02:25:09,280 --> 02:25:10,460
to use all of them.

3717
02:25:14,240 --> 02:25:15,760
Let then the ruling principle

3718
02:25:15,760 --> 02:25:17,540
holding fast to these things

3719
02:25:17,540 --> 02:25:19,060
go straight on,

3720
02:25:19,420 --> 02:25:21,080
and it has what is its own.

3721
02:25:24,950 --> 02:25:26,390
Love that only which happens

3722
02:25:26,390 --> 02:25:26,830
to thee

3723
02:25:26,830 --> 02:25:28,090
and is spun with the thread

3724
02:25:28,090 --> 02:25:29,070
of thy destiny,

3725
02:25:29,700 --> 02:25:30,880
for what is more suitable,

3726
02:25:31,560 --> 02:25:32,920
in everything which happens,

3727
02:25:33,300 --> 02:25:34,740
keep before thy eyes

3728
02:25:34,740 --> 02:25:35,720
those to whom

3729
02:25:35,720 --> 02:25:37,040
the same things happened,

3730
02:25:37,360 --> 02:25:38,680
and how they were vexed

3731
02:25:38,680 --> 02:25:39,420
and treated them

3732
02:25:39,420 --> 02:25:40,480
as strange things,

3733
02:25:40,480 --> 02:25:42,400
and found fault with them,

3734
02:25:42,560 --> 02:25:44,500
and now where are they?

3735
02:25:47,720 --> 02:25:49,220
Why then dost thou too

3736
02:25:49,220 --> 02:25:50,740
choose to act in the same way?

3737
02:25:51,480 --> 02:25:52,780
And why dost thou not leave

3738
02:25:52,780 --> 02:25:54,000
these agitations

3739
02:25:54,000 --> 02:25:55,620
which are foreign to nature,

3740
02:25:56,120 --> 02:25:57,500
to those who cause them,

3741
02:25:57,580 --> 02:25:59,260
and those who are moved by them?

3742
02:26:03,160 --> 02:26:04,560
And why art thou not

3743
02:26:04,560 --> 02:26:05,600
altogether intent

3744
02:26:05,600 --> 02:26:06,660
upon the right way

3745
02:26:06,660 --> 02:26:07,500
of making use

3746
02:26:07,500 --> 02:26:08,120
of the things

3747
02:26:08,120 --> 02:26:09,240
which happen to thee?

3748
02:26:10,880 --> 02:26:13,040
For then thou wilt use them well,

3749
02:26:13,300 --> 02:26:14,820
and they will be a material

3750
02:26:14,820 --> 02:26:16,500
for thee to work on.

3751
02:26:16,820 --> 02:26:19,200
Only attend to thyself,

3752
02:26:19,420 --> 02:26:21,160
and resolve to be a good man

3753
02:26:21,160 --> 02:26:22,260
in every act

3754
02:26:22,260 --> 02:26:23,280
which thou doest.

3755
02:26:24,200 --> 02:26:25,060
And remember,

3756
02:26:27,100 --> 02:26:28,540
the body ought to be compact,

3757
02:26:28,900 --> 02:26:30,700
and to show no new regularity

3758
02:26:30,700 --> 02:26:32,800
either in motion or attitude,

3759
02:26:34,310 --> 02:26:36,190
for what the mind shows in the face,

3760
02:26:36,390 --> 02:26:37,550
by maintaining in it

3761
02:26:37,550 --> 02:26:39,110
the expression of intelligence

3762
02:26:39,110 --> 02:26:40,110
and propriety,

3763
02:26:41,860 --> 02:26:43,240
that ought to be required

3764
02:26:43,240 --> 02:26:45,040
also in the whole body,

3765
02:26:45,420 --> 02:26:46,740
but all of these things

3766
02:26:46,740 --> 02:26:48,280
should be observed

3767
02:26:48,280 --> 02:26:49,720
without affectation.

3768
02:26:51,940 --> 02:26:54,160
The art of life is more like

3769
02:26:54,160 --> 02:26:55,440
the wrestler's art

3770
02:26:55,440 --> 02:26:56,460
than the dancer's,

3771
02:26:56,540 --> 02:26:57,640
in respect of this,

3772
02:26:57,760 --> 02:26:59,080
that it should stand ready

3773
02:26:59,080 --> 02:26:59,920
and firm

3774
02:26:59,920 --> 02:27:01,180
to meet onsets

3775
02:27:01,180 --> 02:27:03,000
which are sudden and unexpected.

3776
02:27:03,500 --> 02:27:04,620
Constantly observe

3777
02:27:04,620 --> 02:27:05,700
who those are,

3778
02:27:06,000 --> 02:27:07,000
whose approbation

3779
02:27:07,000 --> 02:27:08,140
thou wishest to have,

3780
02:27:08,340 --> 02:27:09,700
and what ruling principles

3781
02:27:09,700 --> 02:27:10,520
they possess.

3782
02:27:11,280 --> 02:27:13,280
For then thou wilt neither blame

3783
02:27:13,280 --> 02:27:15,460
those who offend involuntarily,

3784
02:27:15,920 --> 02:27:16,840
nor wilt thou want

3785
02:27:16,840 --> 02:27:17,900
their approbation,

3786
02:27:18,100 --> 02:27:19,620
if thou lookest to the sources

3787
02:27:19,620 --> 02:27:21,440
of their opinions and appetites.

3788
02:27:21,440 --> 02:27:24,020
Every soul, the philosopher says,

3789
02:27:24,480 --> 02:27:27,100
is involuntarily deprived of truth.

3790
02:27:27,620 --> 02:27:29,680
Consequently, in the same way,

3791
02:27:29,980 --> 02:27:31,460
it is deprived of justice

3792
02:27:31,460 --> 02:27:32,360
and temperance

3793
02:27:32,360 --> 02:27:33,540
and benevolence

3794
02:27:33,540 --> 02:27:35,120
and everything of the kind.

3795
02:27:38,720 --> 02:27:39,780
In every pain

3796
02:27:39,780 --> 02:27:41,480
let this thought be present,

3797
02:27:42,220 --> 02:27:44,600
that there is no dishonor in it,

3798
02:27:45,120 --> 02:27:46,060
nor does it make

3799
02:27:46,060 --> 02:27:48,100
the governing intelligence worse,

3800
02:27:48,960 --> 02:27:50,780
for it does not damage

3801
02:27:50,780 --> 02:27:51,760
the intelligence.

3802
02:27:57,430 --> 02:27:58,950
You need to add some text

3803
02:27:58,950 --> 02:27:59,850
for me to talk.

3804
02:28:00,810 --> 02:28:03,030
Indeed, in the case of most pains,

3805
02:28:03,530 --> 02:28:05,990
let this remark of Epicurus aid thee.

3806
02:28:06,430 --> 02:28:08,830
That pain is neither intolerable

3807
02:28:08,830 --> 02:28:09,870
nor everlasting,

3808
02:28:11,170 --> 02:28:12,690
if thou bearest in mind

3809
02:28:12,690 --> 02:28:14,110
that it has its limits,

3810
02:28:14,590 --> 02:28:16,190
and if thou addest nothing

3811
02:28:16,190 --> 02:28:17,550
to it in imagination.

3812
02:28:20,320 --> 02:28:21,560
And remember this, too,

3813
02:28:21,680 --> 02:28:22,920
that we do not perceive

3814
02:28:22,920 --> 02:28:23,840
that many things

3815
02:28:23,840 --> 02:28:25,300
which are disagreeable to us

3816
02:28:25,300 --> 02:28:26,680
are the same as pain,

3817
02:28:27,060 --> 02:28:29,560
such as excessive drowsiness

3818
02:28:29,560 --> 02:28:31,400
and the being scorched by heat

3819
02:28:34,430 --> 02:28:36,050
and the having no appetite.

3820
02:28:36,510 --> 02:28:38,850
When then thou art discontented

3821
02:28:38,850 --> 02:28:40,350
about any of these things,

3822
02:28:40,710 --> 02:28:41,650
say to thyself

3823
02:28:41,650 --> 02:28:43,830
that thou art not yielding to pain.

3824
02:28:48,940 --> 02:28:50,040
You need to add some text

3825
02:28:50,040 --> 02:28:51,020
for me to talk,

3826
02:28:51,700 --> 02:28:52,740
for it is not enough

3827
02:28:52,740 --> 02:28:53,840
that Socrates died

3828
02:28:53,840 --> 02:28:54,880
a more noble death

3829
02:28:54,880 --> 02:28:56,920
and disputed more skillfully

3830
02:28:56,920 --> 02:28:57,980
with the sophists,

3831
02:28:58,460 --> 02:28:59,860
and passed the night in the cold

3832
02:28:59,860 --> 02:29:00,940
with more endurance,

3833
02:29:01,400 --> 02:29:02,620
and that when he was bid

3834
02:29:02,620 --> 02:29:04,400
to arrest Leon of Salamis,

3835
02:29:05,020 --> 02:29:06,640
he considered it more noble

3836
02:29:06,640 --> 02:29:07,520
to refuse,

3837
02:29:07,520 --> 02:29:08,840
and that he walked

3838
02:29:08,840 --> 02:29:10,660
in a swaggering way in the streets.

3839
02:29:11,400 --> 02:29:12,740
Though as to this fact

3840
02:29:12,740 --> 02:29:13,840
one may have great

3841
02:29:14,480 --> 02:29:16,460
what kind of a soul it was

3842
02:29:16,460 --> 02:29:18,080
that Socrates possessed,

3843
02:29:18,600 --> 02:29:20,260
and if he was able to be content

3844
02:29:20,260 --> 02:29:22,000
with being just towards men

3845
02:29:22,000 --> 02:29:24,160
and pious towards the gods,

3846
02:29:24,840 --> 02:29:26,120
neither idly vexed

3847
02:29:26,120 --> 02:29:27,520
on account of men's villainy,

3848
02:29:28,770 --> 02:29:30,870
nor yet making himself a slave

3849
02:29:30,870 --> 02:29:32,350
to any man's ignorance,

3850
02:29:35,460 --> 02:29:37,380
nor enduring it as intolerable,

3851
02:29:37,600 --> 02:29:38,780
nor allowing his understanding

3852
02:29:38,780 --> 02:29:40,220
to sympathize with the affects

3853
02:29:40,220 --> 02:29:41,420
of the miserable flesh.

3854
02:29:42,060 --> 02:29:43,780
Nature has not so mingled

3855
02:29:43,780 --> 02:29:44,580
the intelligence

3856
02:29:44,580 --> 02:29:46,420
with the composition of the body,

3857
02:29:47,000 --> 02:29:48,380
