3880
02:30:25,980 --> 02:30:28,020
in the greatest tranquillity of mind,

3881
02:30:28,980 --> 02:30:30,200
even if all the world

3882
02:30:30,200 --> 02:30:31,340
cry out against thee

3883
02:30:31,340 --> 02:30:32,740
as much as they choose.

3884
02:30:38,170 --> 02:30:38,630
NAND!

3885
02:30:40,900 --> 02:30:42,480
For what hinders the mind,

3886
02:30:42,680 --> 02:30:44,120
in the midst of all this,

3887
02:30:44,120 --> 02:30:45,580
from maintaining itself

3888
02:30:45,580 --> 02:30:46,760
in tranquillity,

3889
02:30:46,980 --> 02:30:48,140
and in a just judgment

3890
02:30:48,140 --> 02:30:49,740
of all surrounding things,

3891
02:30:50,360 --> 02:30:51,840
and in a ready use

3892
02:30:51,840 --> 02:30:52,660
of the objects

3893
02:30:52,660 --> 02:30:54,180
which are presented to it,

3894
02:30:54,600 --> 02:30:56,280
so that the judgment may say

3895
02:30:56,280 --> 02:30:57,460
to the thing which falls

3896
02:30:57,460 --> 02:30:58,760
under its observation,

3897
02:30:59,840 --> 02:31:00,700
This thou art,

3898
02:31:00,860 --> 02:31:01,680
in substance,

3899
02:31:02,080 --> 02:31:02,520
reality.

3900
02:31:04,680 --> 02:31:06,120
You need to add some text

3901
02:31:06,120 --> 02:31:07,000
for me to talk.

3902
02:31:07,660 --> 02:31:08,680
My est appear to be

3903
02:31:08,680 --> 02:31:09,680
of a different kind,

3904
02:31:09,980 --> 02:31:11,620
and the use shall say to that

3905
02:31:11,620 --> 02:31:13,140
which falls under the hand,

3906
02:31:13,680 --> 02:31:14,840
Thou art the thing

3907
02:31:14,840 --> 02:31:15,760
that I was seeking.

3908
02:31:16,420 --> 02:31:18,480
For to me that which presents itself

3909
02:31:18,480 --> 02:31:20,660
is always a material for virtue,

3910
02:31:20,940 --> 02:31:22,700
both rational and political,

3911
02:31:23,220 --> 02:31:24,320
and, in a word,

3912
02:31:24,780 --> 02:31:26,380
for the exercise of art,

3913
02:31:26,820 --> 02:31:28,840
which belongs to man or God.

3914
02:31:29,360 --> 02:31:30,540
For everything which happens

3915
02:31:30,540 --> 02:31:31,520
has a relationship

3916
02:31:31,520 --> 02:31:32,940
either to God or man,

3917
02:31:33,160 --> 02:31:34,180
and is neither new

3918
02:31:34,180 --> 02:31:35,440
nor difficult to handle,

3919
02:31:35,700 --> 02:31:37,460
but usual and apt matter

3920
02:31:37,460 --> 02:31:38,140
to work on.

3921
02:31:38,540 --> 02:31:40,180
The perfection of moral character

3922
02:31:40,180 --> 02:31:41,140
consists in this,

3923
02:31:41,420 --> 02:31:43,360
in passing every day as the last,

3924
02:31:43,480 --> 02:31:44,360
and in being neither

3925
02:31:44,360 --> 02:31:45,420
violently excited,

3926
02:31:45,680 --> 02:31:46,240
nor torpid,

3927
02:31:46,440 --> 02:31:47,660
nor playing the hypocrite.

3928
02:31:48,040 --> 02:31:49,500
The gods who are immortal

3929
02:31:49,500 --> 02:31:50,520
are not vexed

3930
02:31:50,520 --> 02:31:52,260
because during so long a time

3931
02:31:52,260 --> 02:31:54,360
they must tolerate continually.

3932
02:31:55,440 --> 02:31:56,780
Men such as they are,

3933
02:31:56,880 --> 02:31:58,340
and so many of them bad.

3934
02:32:01,770 --> 02:32:02,390
But thou,

3935
02:32:02,530 --> 02:32:04,470
who art destined to end so soon,

3936
02:32:04,770 --> 02:32:05,590
art thou wearied

3937
02:32:05,590 --> 02:32:06,710
of enduring the bad,

3938
02:32:07,050 --> 02:32:07,990
and this too,

3939
02:32:08,170 --> 02:32:09,390
when thou art one of them.

3940
02:32:14,120 --> 02:32:15,460
Whatever the rational

3941
02:32:15,460 --> 02:32:17,780
and political, social faculty

3942
02:32:17,780 --> 02:32:19,440
finds to be neither intelligent

3943
02:32:19,440 --> 02:32:20,380
nor social,

3944
02:32:20,380 --> 02:32:21,740
it properly judges

3945
02:32:21,740 --> 02:32:23,520
to be inferior to itself.

3946
02:32:24,200 --> 02:32:26,000
And when thou hast done a good act

3947
02:32:26,000 --> 02:32:27,600
and another has received it,

3948
02:32:27,900 --> 02:32:28,960
why dost thou look

3949
02:32:28,960 --> 02:32:29,820
for a third thing

3950
02:32:29,820 --> 02:32:30,800
besides these,

3951
02:32:30,900 --> 02:32:31,940
as fools do,

3952
02:32:32,300 --> 02:32:33,800
either to have the reputation

3953
02:32:33,800 --> 02:32:35,120
of having done a good act,

3954
02:32:35,300 --> 02:32:36,580
or to obtain a return?

3955
02:32:37,220 --> 02:32:38,960
No man is tired of receiving

3956
02:32:38,960 --> 02:32:39,780
what is useful.

3957
02:32:40,460 --> 02:32:41,700
But it is useful

3958
02:32:41,700 --> 02:32:43,360
to act according to nature.

3959
02:32:47,010 --> 02:32:48,330
Do not then be tired

3960
02:32:48,330 --> 02:32:49,730
of receiving what is useful

3961
02:32:49,730 --> 02:32:51,010
by doing it to others.

3962
02:32:53,950 --> 02:32:54,990
But now,

3963
02:32:55,130 --> 02:32:57,150
either everything that takes place

3964
02:32:57,150 --> 02:32:58,950
comes by way of consequence

3965
02:32:58,950 --> 02:33:00,330
or continuity,

3966
02:33:00,850 --> 02:33:02,150
or even the chief things

3967
02:33:02,150 --> 02:33:03,130
towards which

3968
02:33:03,130 --> 02:33:05,210
the ruling power of the universe

3969
02:33:05,210 --> 02:33:06,690
directs its own movement

3970
02:33:06,690 --> 02:33:07,570
are governed

3971
02:33:07,570 --> 02:33:09,410
by no rational principle.

3972
02:33:10,050 --> 02:33:11,050
If this is remembered,

3973
02:33:11,110 --> 02:33:12,470
it will make thee more tranquil

3974
02:33:12,470 --> 02:33:13,510
in many things.

3975
02:33:14,740 --> 02:33:15,780
Book 8

3976
02:33:15,780 --> 02:33:18,400
This reflection also tends

3977
02:33:18,400 --> 02:33:19,300
to the removal

3978
02:33:19,300 --> 02:33:21,520
of the desire of empty fame,

3979
02:33:21,940 --> 02:33:23,280
that it is no longer

3980
02:33:23,280 --> 02:33:24,160
in thy power

3981
02:33:24,160 --> 02:33:24,820
to have lived

3982
02:33:24,820 --> 02:33:26,220
the whole of thy life,

3983
02:33:26,540 --> 02:33:27,880
or at least thy life

3984
02:33:27,880 --> 02:33:29,360
from thy youth upwards,

3985
02:33:29,820 --> 02:33:30,780
like a philosopher.

3986
02:33:34,020 --> 02:33:35,820
But both to many others

3987
02:33:35,820 --> 02:33:37,220
and to thyself

3988
02:33:37,220 --> 02:33:39,280
it is plain that thou,

3989
02:33:39,600 --> 02:33:40,640
thou hast fallen

3990
02:33:40,640 --> 02:33:41,900
into disorder then

3991
02:33:41,900 --> 02:33:43,160
so that it is no longer

3992
02:33:43,160 --> 02:33:43,980
easy for thee

3993
02:33:43,980 --> 02:33:45,060
to get the reputation

3994
02:33:45,060 --> 02:33:46,060
of a philosopher,

3995
02:33:46,780 --> 02:33:47,920
and thy plan of life

3996
02:33:47,920 --> 02:33:49,540
also opposes it.

3997
02:33:49,860 --> 02:33:52,000
If then thou hast truly seen

3998
02:33:52,000 --> 02:33:53,180
where the matter lies,

3999
02:33:53,540 --> 02:33:54,460
throw away the thought

4000
02:33:54,460 --> 02:33:56,520
how thou shalt seem to others,

4001
02:33:57,060 --> 02:33:58,120
and be content

4002
02:33:58,120 --> 02:33:59,260
if thou shalt live

4003
02:33:59,260 --> 02:34:00,400
the rest of thy life

4004
02:34:00,400 --> 02:34:01,420
in such wise

4005
02:34:01,420 --> 02:34:02,760
as thy nature wills.

4006
02:34:03,660 --> 02:34:05,240
Observe then what it wills,

4007
02:34:05,280 --> 02:34:06,220
and let nothing else

4008
02:34:06,220 --> 02:34:07,240
distract thee,

4009
02:34:07,600 --> 02:34:09,120
for thou hast had experience

4010
02:34:09,120 --> 02:34:10,160
of many wanderings

4011
02:34:10,160 --> 02:34:11,100
without having found

4012
02:34:11,100 --> 02:34:12,100
happiness anywhere,

4013
02:34:12,820 --> 02:34:13,960
not in syllogisms,

4014
02:34:14,340 --> 02:34:15,100
nor in wealth,

4015
02:34:15,520 --> 02:34:16,540
nor in reputation,

4016
02:34:17,000 --> 02:34:17,860
nor in enjoyment,

4017
02:34:18,660 --> 02:34:19,440
nor anywhere.

4018
02:34:20,060 --> 02:34:21,080
Where is it then?

4019
02:34:21,520 --> 02:34:23,040
In doing what man's

4020
02:34:23,040 --> 02:34:24,160
nature requires.

4021
02:34:24,460 --> 02:34:26,300
How then shall a man do

4022
02:34:26,300 --> 02:34:27,000
in this?

4023
02:34:27,840 --> 02:34:28,800
If he has principles

4024
02:34:28,800 --> 02:34:29,460
from which come

4025
02:34:29,460 --> 02:34:30,100
his effects

4026
02:34:30,100 --> 02:34:30,980
and his acts,

4027
02:34:31,280 --> 02:34:32,100
what principles?

4028
02:34:33,280 --> 02:34:34,220
Those which relate

4029
02:34:34,220 --> 02:34:35,220
to good and bad,

4030
02:34:35,520 --> 02:34:36,060
the belief that

4031
02:34:36,060 --> 02:34:36,880
there is nothing good

4032
02:34:36,880 --> 02:34:37,440
for man

4033
02:34:37,440 --> 02:34:38,500
which does not make

4034
02:34:38,500 --> 02:34:39,140
him just,

4035
02:34:39,460 --> 02:34:39,840
temperate,

4036
02:34:40,140 --> 02:34:40,480
manly,

4037
02:34:40,620 --> 02:34:40,920
free,

4038
02:34:41,180 --> 02:34:41,920
and that there is

4039
02:34:41,920 --> 02:34:42,680
nothing bad

4040
02:34:42,680 --> 02:34:43,780
which does not.

4041
02:34:44,140 --> 02:34:44,900
On the occasion

4042
02:34:44,900 --> 02:34:46,000
of every act,

4043
02:34:46,460 --> 02:34:47,280
ask thyself

4044
02:34:47,280 --> 02:34:48,080
how is this

4045
02:34:48,080 --> 02:34:49,300
with respect to me?

4046
02:34:49,660 --> 02:34:51,000
Shall I repent of it?

4047
02:35:02,030 --> 02:35:02,930
A little time,

4048
02:35:03,090 --> 02:35:03,910
and I am dead,

4049
02:35:04,190 --> 02:35:05,030
and all is gone.

4050
02:35:05,150 --> 02:35:06,950
What more do I seek

4051
02:35:06,950 --> 02:35:08,350
if what I am now doing

4052
02:35:08,350 --> 02:35:09,230
is work of an

4053
02:35:09,230 --> 02:35:10,410
intelligent living being

4054
02:35:10,410 --> 02:35:11,730
and a social being

4055
02:35:11,730 --> 02:35:12,790
and one who is under

4056
02:35:12,790 --> 02:35:14,270
