02:37:35,520 --> 02:37:36,740
Thou hast not leisure

4151
02:37:36,740 --> 02:37:38,200
or ability to read,

4152
02:37:38,920 --> 02:37:39,960
but thou hast leisure

4153
02:37:39,960 --> 02:37:41,800
or ability to check arrogance.

4154
02:37:42,540 --> 02:37:43,440
Thou hast leisure

4155
02:37:43,440 --> 02:37:44,300
to be superior

4156
02:37:44,300 --> 02:37:45,600
to pleasure and pain.

4157
02:37:46,330 --> 02:37:47,230
Thou hast leisure

4158
02:37:47,230 --> 02:37:48,070
to be superior

4159
02:37:48,070 --> 02:37:49,070
to love of fame,

4160
02:37:49,070 --> 02:37:50,770
and not to be vexed

4161
02:37:50,770 --> 02:37:52,320
at stupid and ungrateful people,

4162
02:37:53,410 --> 02:37:54,930
nay, even to care for them.

4163
02:37:55,590 --> 02:37:57,050
Let no man any longer

4164
02:37:57,050 --> 02:37:58,490
hear thee finding fault

4165
02:37:58,490 --> 02:37:59,790
with the court life

4166
02:37:59,790 --> 02:38:00,930
or with thy own,

4167
02:38:04,020 --> 02:38:05,160
but no such man

4168
02:38:05,160 --> 02:38:06,100
would ever repent

4169
02:38:06,100 --> 02:38:07,400
of having refused

4170
02:38:07,400 --> 02:38:08,780
any sensual pleasure.

4171
02:38:10,770 --> 02:38:11,890
Pleasure, then,

4172
02:38:12,030 --> 02:38:13,810
is neither good nor useful.

4173
02:38:14,950 --> 02:38:15,830
This thing,

4174
02:38:16,210 --> 02:38:17,810
what is it in itself,

4175
02:38:18,110 --> 02:38:19,630
in its own constitution?

4176
02:38:20,450 --> 02:38:21,690
What is its substance

4177
02:38:21,690 --> 02:38:22,410
and material?

4178
02:38:23,030 --> 02:38:24,730
And what its causal nature

4179
02:38:24,730 --> 02:38:25,770
or form?

4180
02:38:26,250 --> 02:38:26,970
And what is it doing

4181
02:38:26,970 --> 02:38:27,670
in the world?

4182
02:38:28,090 --> 02:38:29,330
And how long does it subsist?

4183
02:38:30,830 --> 02:38:31,830
When thou risest

4184
02:38:31,830 --> 02:38:33,190
from sleep with reluctance,

4185
02:38:34,330 --> 02:38:35,310
remember that it is

4186
02:38:35,310 --> 02:38:37,050
according to thy constitution

4187
02:38:37,590 --> 02:38:39,390
and according to human nature

4188
02:38:39,390 --> 02:38:41,010
to perform social acts.

4189
02:38:41,900 --> 02:38:43,840
But sleeping is common also

4190
02:38:43,840 --> 02:38:45,460
to irrational animals.

4191
02:38:46,100 --> 02:38:47,360
But that which is according

4192
02:38:47,360 --> 02:38:48,840
to each individual's nature

4193
02:38:48,840 --> 02:38:50,640
is also more peculiarly

4194
02:38:50,640 --> 02:38:52,220
its own and more suitable

4195
02:38:52,220 --> 02:38:53,060
to its nature,

4196
02:38:53,360 --> 02:38:55,440
and indeed also more agreeable.

4197
02:38:55,980 --> 02:38:57,020
Constantly and,

4198
02:38:57,020 --> 02:38:58,120
if it be possible,

4199
02:38:58,540 --> 02:38:59,720
on the occasion of every

4200
02:38:59,720 --> 02:39:00,920
impression on the soul,

4201
02:39:01,360 --> 02:39:02,400
apply to it the principles

4202
02:39:02,400 --> 02:39:04,040
of physic, of ethic,

4203
02:39:04,320 --> 02:39:05,420
and of dialectic.

4204
02:39:05,880 --> 02:39:07,800
Whatever man thou meetest with,

4205
02:39:08,160 --> 02:39:09,760
immediately say to thyself,

4206
02:39:10,140 --> 02:39:11,800
What opinions has this man

4207
02:39:11,800 --> 02:39:13,600
about good and bad?

4208
02:39:14,040 --> 02:39:15,580
For if, with respect to

4209
02:39:15,580 --> 02:39:16,640
pleasure and pain

4210
02:39:16,640 --> 02:39:18,060
and the causes of each,

4211
02:39:18,500 --> 02:39:20,040
and with respect to fame

4212
02:39:20,040 --> 02:39:20,960
and ignominy,

4213
02:39:20,960 --> 02:39:22,300
death and life,

4214
02:39:22,540 --> 02:39:24,340
he has such and such opinions,

4215
02:39:29,060 --> 02:39:30,520
will seem nothing wonderful

4216
02:39:30,520 --> 02:39:31,940
or strange to me.

4217
02:39:34,160 --> 02:39:35,960
Remember that as it is ashamed

4218
02:39:35,960 --> 02:39:36,840
to be surprised

4219
02:39:36,840 --> 02:39:39,080
if the fig tree produces figs,

4220
02:39:39,120 --> 02:39:40,480
so it is to be surprised

4221
02:39:40,480 --> 02:39:41,860
if the world produces

4222
02:39:41,860 --> 02:39:43,240
such and such things,

4223
02:39:43,460 --> 02:39:45,040
of which it is productive.

4224
02:39:48,540 --> 02:39:49,540
Remember that,

4225
02:39:49,740 --> 02:39:51,140
to change thy opinion

4226
02:39:51,140 --> 02:39:52,580
and to follow him

4227
02:39:52,580 --> 02:39:53,960
who corrects thy error

4228
02:39:53,960 --> 02:39:56,080
is as consistent with freedom

4229
02:39:56,080 --> 02:39:57,800
as it is to persist

4230
02:39:57,800 --> 02:39:59,100
in thy error.

4231
02:39:59,850 --> 02:40:01,550
For it is thy own,

4232
02:40:01,850 --> 02:40:03,890
and the activity which is exerted,

4233
02:40:04,010 --> 02:40:05,430
according to thy own movement

4234
02:40:05,430 --> 02:40:06,210
and judgment,

4235
02:40:06,950 --> 02:40:07,790
and indeed,

4236
02:40:08,430 --> 02:40:09,650
according to thy own

4237
02:40:09,650 --> 02:40:10,890
understanding too.

4238
02:40:11,450 --> 02:40:13,470
If a thing is in thy own power,

4239
02:40:13,830 --> 02:40:15,090
why dost thou do it?

4240
02:40:15,630 --> 02:40:16,830
But if it is in the power

4241
02:40:16,830 --> 02:40:17,450
of another,

4242
02:40:17,810 --> 02:40:18,890
whom dost thou blame?

4243
02:40:19,350 --> 02:40:20,210
The atoms,

4244
02:40:20,450 --> 02:40:20,910
chance,

4245
02:40:21,130 --> 02:40:21,790
or the gods?

4246
02:40:22,980 --> 02:40:24,420
Both are foolish.

4247
02:40:29,720 --> 02:40:31,120
For if thou canst,

4248
02:40:31,480 --> 02:40:33,160
correct that which is the cause.

4249
02:40:33,240 --> 02:40:35,280
But if thou canst not do this,

4250
02:40:35,620 --> 02:40:37,180
correct at least the thing itself.

4251
02:40:37,940 --> 02:40:40,340
But if thou canst not do even this,

4252
02:40:42,900 --> 02:40:44,300
for nothing should be done

4253
02:40:44,300 --> 02:40:45,300
without a purpose.

4254
02:40:46,380 --> 02:40:47,360
That which is died

4255
02:40:47,360 --> 02:40:49,200
falls not out of the universe.

4256
02:40:53,940 --> 02:40:55,320
And these too change,

4257
02:40:55,760 --> 02:40:57,000
and they murmur not.

4258
02:41:02,220 --> 02:41:04,260
Everything exists for some end,

4259
02:41:04,500 --> 02:41:05,400
a horse,

4260
02:41:05,660 --> 02:41:06,220
a vine.

4261
02:41:06,680 --> 02:41:07,720
Why dost thou wonder?

4262
02:41:08,570 --> 02:41:09,810
Even the sun will say,

4263
02:41:10,150 --> 02:41:11,370
I am for some purpose,

4264
02:41:11,550 --> 02:41:12,530
and the rest of the gods

4265
02:41:12,530 --> 02:41:13,530
will say the same.

4266
02:41:13,770 --> 02:41:14,870
For what purpose?

4267
02:41:15,590 --> 02:41:16,530
Then art thou.

4268
02:41:19,260 --> 02:41:20,200
What good is it then

4269
02:41:20,200 --> 02:41:21,700
for the ball to be thrown up?

4270
02:41:22,040 --> 02:41:23,620
Or harm for it to come down,

4271
02:41:23,760 --> 02:41:24,840
or even to have fallen?

4272
02:41:25,380 --> 02:41:27,440
And what good is it to the bubble

4273
02:41:27,440 --> 02:41:28,700
while it holds together?

4274
02:41:29,120 --> 02:41:30,860
Or what harm when it is burst?

4275
02:41:34,140 --> 02:41:35,780
Turn it, the body,

4276
02:41:36,220 --> 02:41:37,020
inside out,

4277
02:41:37,240 --> 02:41:38,600
and see what kind of thing it is.

4278
02:41:38,840 --> 02:41:40,140
And when it has grown old,

4279
02:41:40,480 --> 02:41:41,780
what kind of thing it becomes,

4280
02:41:42,120 --> 02:41:43,660
and when it is diseased.

4281
02:41:44,300 --> 02:41:45,580
Short-lived are both

4282
02:41:45,580 --> 02:41:47,100
the praiser and the praised.

4283
02:41:47,700 --> 02:41:49,180
And the rememberer

4284
02:41:49,180 --> 02:41:50,060
and the remembered.

4285
02:41:50,780 --> 02:41:52,020
And all this in a nook

4286
02:41:52,020 --> 02:41:53,320
of this part of the world.

4287
02:41:53,860 --> 02:41:55,660
And not even here do all agree,

4288
02:41:56,020 --> 02:41:57,620
no, not any one with.

4289
02:41:58,220 --> 02:41:59,080
Attend to the matter

4290
02:41:59,080 --> 02:42:00,180
which is before thee,

4291
02:42:00,400 --> 02:42:01,600
whether it is an opinion,

4292
02:42:01,760 --> 02:42:03,040
or an act, or a word.

4293
02:42:03,720 --> 02:42:05,300
Thou suffer'st this justly,

4294
02:42:05,480 --> 02:42:06,660
for thou choosest rather

4295
02:42:06,660 --> 02:42:08,160
to become good to-morrow

4296
02:42:08,160 --> 02:42:09,540
than to be good to-day.

4297
02:42:11,270 --> 02:42:12,810
I do it with reference

4298
02:42:12,810 --> 02:42:14,170
to the good of mankind.

4299
02:42:15,140 --> 02:42:16,660
Does anything happen to me?

4300
02:42:17,340 --> 02:42:18,520
I receive it,

4301
02:42:18,560 --> 02:42:19,880
and refer it to the gods,

4302
02:42:20,400 --> 02:42:21,960
and the source of all things,

4303
02:42:22,320 --> 02:42:23,540
from which all that happens

4304
02:42:23,540 --> 02:42:24,440
is derived.

4305
02:42:25,360 --> 02:42:27,980
Such as bathing appears to thee,

4306
02:42:28,420 --> 02:42:31,140
oil, sweat, dirt, filthy water,

4307
02:42:31,560 --> 02:42:32,760
all things disgusting,

4308
02:42:33,180 --> 02:42:34,460
so is every part of life

4309
02:42:34,460 --> 02:42:35,220
and everything.

4310
02:42:35,940 --> 02:42:37,480
Lucilla saw Verus die,

4311
02:42:37,660 --> 02:42:38,860
and then Lucilla died.

4312
02:42:39,620 --> 02:42:41,200
Secunda saw Maximus die,

4313
02:42:41,260 --> 02:42:42,700
and then Secunda died.

4314
02:42:45,010 --> 02:42:46,950
Epitensionist saw Diotimus die,

4315
02:42:47,070 --> 02:42:48,470
and Epitensionist died.

4316
02:42:54,010 --> 02:42:55,810
Such is everything.

4317
02:42:56,700 --> 02:42:58,300
Seller saw Hadrian die,

4318
02:42:58,340 --> 02:42:59,660
and then Seller died,

4319
02:43:04,280 --> 02:43:06,580
all ephemeral, dead long ago.

4320
02:43:07,200 --> 02:43:09,120
Some indeed have not been remembered

4321
02:43:09,120 --> 02:43:10,580
even for a short time,

4322
02:43:10,860 --> 02:43:11,940
and others have become

4323
02:43:11,940 --> 02:43:13,120
the heroes of fables,

4324
02:43:13,380 --> 02:43:15,080
and again others have disappeared

4325
02:43:15,080 --> 02:43:16,160
even from fables.

4326
02:43:17,140 --> 02:43:18,380
Remember this then,

4327
02:43:18,880 --> 02:43:20,460
that this little compound,

4328
02:43:20,860 --> 02:43:23,120
thy self, must either be dissolved,

4329
02:43:23,500 --> 02:43:24,740
or thy poor breath

4330
02:43:24,740 --> 02:43:25,920
must be extinguished,

4331
02:43:26,160 --> 02:43:27,220
or be removed

4332
02:43:27,220 --> 02:43:28,340
and placed elsewhere.

4333
02:43:28,900 --> 02:43:30,960
It is satisfaction to a man

4334
02:43:30,960 --> 02:43:32,980
to do the proper works of a man.

4335
02:43:33,540 --> 02:43:35,920
Now it is a proper work of a man

4336
02:43:35,920 --> 02:43:38,720
to be in benevolent to his own kind,

4337
02:43:39,020 --> 02:43:41,320
to despise the movements of the senses,

4338
02:43:41,860 --> 02:43:43,680
to form a just judgment

4339
02:43:43,680 --> 02:43:45,020
of plausible appearances,

4340
02:43:45,340 --> 02:43:46,340
and to take a survey

4341
02:43:46,340 --> 02:43:47,900
of the nature of the universe

4342
02:43:47,900 --> 02:43:50,240
and of the things which happen in it.

4343
02:43:50,680 --> 02:43:51,840
There are three relations

4344
02:43:51,840 --> 02:43:53,680
between thee and other things,

4345
02:43:53,940 --> 02:43:55,000
the one to the body

4346
02:43:55,000 --> 02:43:56,120
which surrounds thee,

4347
02:43:56,120 --> 02:43:58,380
the second to the divine cause

4348
02:43:58,380 --> 02:44:00,440
from which all things come to all,

4349
02:44:00,580 --> 02:44:02,680
and the third to those who live with thee.

4350
02:44:03,060 --> 02:44:05,060
Pain is either an evil to the body,

4351
02:44:05,260 --> 02:44:06,380
then let the body say

4352
02:44:06,380 --> 02:44:07,540
what it thinks of it,

4353
02:44:07,560 --> 02:44:08,520
or to the soul.

4354
02:44:09,060 --> 02:44:10,760
But it is in the power of the soul

4355
02:44:10,760 --> 02:44:12,440
to maintain its own serenity

4356
02:44:12,440 --> 02:44:13,400
and tranquility,

4357
02:44:13,580 --> 02:44:14,540
and not to think

4358
02:44:14,540 --> 02:44:15,700
that pain is an evil.

4359
02:44:16,140 --> 02:44:17,060
For every judgment

4360
02:44:17,060 --> 02:44:18,520
and movement and desire

4361
02:44:18,520 --> 02:44:19,840
and aversion is within,

4362
02:44:20,260 --> 02:44:22,000
and no evil ascends so high.

4363
02:44:23,050 --> 02:44:24,510
Wipe out thy imaginations

4364
02:44:24,510 --> 02:44:26,110
by often saying to thyself,

4365
02:44:26,350 --> 02:44:28,430
Now it is in my power

4366
02:44:28,430 --> 02:44:30,770
to let no badness be in this soul,

4367
02:44:31,950 --> 02:44:32,810
nor desire,

4368
02:44:33,590 --> 02:44:35,380
nor any perturbation at all.

4369
02:44:40,800 --> 02:44:41,820
Remember this power

4370
02:44:41,820 --> 02:44:43,580
which thou hast from nature.

4371
02:44:46,140 --> 02:44:47,240
Speak both in the Senate

4372
02:44:47,240 --> 02:44:48,340
and to every man,

4373
02:44:48,560 --> 02:44:49,500
whoever he may be,

4374
02:44:49,740 --> 02:44:50,160
appropriately,

4375
02:44:50,380 --> 02:44:51,820
not with any affectation,

4376
02:44:52,020 --> 02:44:53,300
use plain discourse.

4377
02:44:54,350 --> 02:44:55,370
Augustus's court,

4378
02:44:55,790 --> 02:44:56,910
wife, daughter,

4379
02:44:57,250 --> 02:44:59,250
descendants, ancestors, sister,

4380
02:44:59,790 --> 02:45:01,370
Agrippa, kinsmen,

4381
02:45:01,690 --> 02:45:03,130
intimates, friends,

4382
02:45:03,130 --> 02:45:04,650
Aureus, Messinus,

4383
02:45:05,410 --> 02:45:07,470
physicians and sacrificing priests,

4384
02:45:07,990 --> 02:45:09,410
the whole court is.

4385
02:45:09,670 --> 02:45:10,950
Then turn to the rest,

4386
02:45:11,370 --> 02:45:12,690
not considering the death

4387
02:45:12,690 --> 02:45:13,750
of a single man,

4388
02:45:14,270 --> 02:45:15,470
but of a whole race,

4389
02:45:15,770 --> 02:45:16,730
as of the Pompeii,

4390
02:45:17,470 --> 02:45:18,870
and that which is inscribed

4391
02:45:18,870 --> 02:45:19,770
on the tombs,

4392
02:45:20,010 --> 02:45:21,410
the last of his race.

4393
02:45:21,970 --> 02:45:23,350
Then consider what trouble

4394
02:45:23,350 --> 02:45:24,890
those before them have had

4395
02:45:24,890 --> 02:45:26,630
that they might leave a successor.

4396
02:45:27,190 --> 02:45:29,210
And then, that of necessity,

4397
02:45:29,670 --> 02:45:30,930
some one must be the last.

4398
02:45:31,450 --> 02:45:32,410
Again here,

4399
02:45:32,410 --> 02:45:34,670
consider the death of a whole race.

4400
02:45:35,720 --> 02:45:36,920
In it is thy duty

4401
02:45:36,920 --> 02:45:38,480
to order thy life well

4402
02:45:38,480 --> 02:45:39,840
in every single act,

4403
02:45:40,180 --> 02:45:41,860
and if every act does its duty

4404
02:45:41,860 --> 02:45:43,180
as far as is possible,

4405
02:45:43,640 --> 02:45:44,260
be content,

4406
02:45:44,720 --> 02:45:46,440
and no one is able to hinder thee

4407
02:45:46,440 --> 02:45:47,680
so that each act

4408
02:45:47,680 --> 02:45:49,000
shall not do its duty.

4409
02:45:49,500 --> 02:45:50,840
But something external

4410
02:45:50,840 --> 02:45:52,300
will stand in the way.

4411
02:45:52,840 --> 02:45:54,380
Nothing will stand in the way

4412
02:45:54,380 --> 02:45:55,960
of thy acting justly,

4413
02:45:56,200 --> 02:45:56,960
and soberly,

4414
02:45:57,060 --> 02:45:57,860
and considerately.

4415
02:45:58,770 --> 02:46:00,970
But perhaps some other act of power

4416
02:46:00,970 --> 02:46:02,030
will be hindered.

4417
02:46:02,030 --> 02:46:05,050
Well, but, by acquiescing

4418
02:46:05,050 --> 02:46:05,930
in the hindrance,

4419
02:46:06,210 --> 02:46:07,350
and by being content

4420
02:46:07,350 --> 02:46:08,690
to transfer thy efforts

4421
02:46:08,690 --> 02:46:09,990
to that which is allowed,

4422
02:46:10,450 --> 02:46:11,970
another opportunity of action

4423
02:46:11,970 --> 02:46:13,130
is immediately put,

4424
02:46:13,450 --> 02:46:14,450
before thee,

4425
02:46:14,610 --> 02:46:17,050
in place of that which was hindered,

4426
02:46:17,700 --> 02:46:19,660
and one which will adapt itself

4427
02:46:19,660 --> 02:46:20,580
to this ordering

4428
02:46:20,580 --> 02:46:21,920
of which we are speaking.

4429
02:46:22,300 --> 02:46:24,380
Receive wealth or prosperity

4430
02:46:24,380 --> 02:46:25,360
without arrogance,

4431
02:46:29,070 --> 02:46:30,470
if thou dost ever see

4432
02:46:30,470 --> 02:46:31,590
a hand cut off,

4433
02:46:31,890 --> 02:46:32,570
or a foot,

4434
02:46:32,830 --> 02:46:33,630
or a head,

4435
02:46:33,630 --> 02:46:35,290
lying anywhere apart

4436
02:46:35,290 --> 02:46:36,470
from the rest of the body.

4437
02:46:40,140 --> 02:46:42,360
Such does a man make himself

4438
02:46:42,360 --> 02:46:43,640
as far as he can,

4439
02:46:44,140 --> 02:46:45,240
who is not content

4440
02:46:45,240 --> 02:46:46,100
with what happens

4441
02:46:46,100 --> 02:46:47,900
and separates himself from others,

4442
02:46:48,280 --> 02:46:49,640
or does anything unsocial.

4443
02:46:50,580 --> 02:46:52,020
Suppose that thou hast

4444
02:46:52,020 --> 02:46:53,140
detached thyself

4445
02:46:53,140 --> 02:46:54,560
from the natural unity,

4446
02:46:55,380 --> 02:46:57,820
for thou wast made by nature apart.

4447
02:47:02,830 --> 02:47:04,090
God has allowed this

4448
02:47:04,090 --> 02:47:05,070
to no other part,

4449
02:47:05,450 --> 02:47:06,790
after it has been separated

4450
02:47:06,790 --> 02:47:07,810
and cut asunder,

4451
02:47:08,190 --> 02:47:09,530
to come together again.

4452
02:47:09,910 --> 02:47:11,290
But consider the kindness

4453
02:47:11,290 --> 02:47:13,170
by which he has distinguished man,

4454
02:47:13,450 --> 02:47:15,290
for he has put it in his power

4455
02:47:15,290 --> 02:47:17,250
not to be separated at all

4456
02:47:17,250 --> 02:47:18,170
from the universal,

4457
02:47:18,490 --> 02:47:20,110
and when he has been separated,

4458
02:47:20,370 --> 02:47:22,050
he has allowed him to return

4459
02:47:22,050 --> 02:47:23,210
and to be united

4460
02:47:23,210 --> 02:47:25,310
and to resume his place.

4461
02:47:25,930 --> 02:47:27,690
As the nature of the universal

4462
02:47:27,690 --> 02:47:29,690
has given to every rational being

4463
02:47:29,690 --> 02:47:31,750
all the other powers that it has,

4464
02:47:32,250 --> 02:47:33,750
so we have received from it

4465
02:47:33,750 --> 02:47:35,010
this power also.

4466
02:47:35,490 --> 02:47:37,470
For as the universal nature

4467
02:47:37,470 --> 02:47:38,810
converts and fixes

4468
02:47:38,810 --> 02:47:41,370
in its impredestined place,

4469
02:47:44,070 --> 02:47:45,650
everything which stands in the way

4470
02:47:45,650 --> 02:47:46,510
and opposes it,

4471
02:47:47,520 --> 02:47:48,540
and makes such things

4472
02:47:48,540 --> 02:47:49,480
a part of itself,

4473
02:47:50,410 --> 02:47:52,110
so also the rational animal

4474
02:47:52,110 --> 02:47:54,630
is able to make every hindrance

4475
02:47:54,630 --> 02:47:55,690
its own material,

4476
02:47:56,270 --> 02:47:57,930
and to use it for such purposes

4477
02:47:57,930 --> 02:47:59,550
as it may have designed,

4478
02:48:00,030 --> 02:48:01,370
do not disturb thyself

4479
02:48:01,370 --> 02:48:03,690
by thinking of the whole of thy life.

4480
02:48:04,420 --> 02:48:06,100
Let not thy thoughts at once

4481
02:48:06,100 --> 02:48:07,860
embrace all the various troubles

4482
02:48:07,860 --> 02:48:09,200
which thou mayst expect

4483
02:48:09,200 --> 02:48:10,060
to befall thee,

4484
02:48:10,680 --> 02:48:12,160
but on every occasion

4485
02:48:12,160 --> 02:48:13,360
ask thyself,

4486
02:48:13,900 --> 02:48:15,460
What is there in this

4487
02:48:15,460 --> 02:48:16,660
which is intolerable

4488
02:48:16,660 --> 02:48:17,940
and past-bearing?

4489
02:48:18,300 --> 02:48:20,300
For thou wilt be ashamed to confess.

4490
02:48:20,820 --> 02:48:21,860
In the next place,

4491
02:48:22,200 --> 02:48:23,700
remember that neither the future

4492
02:48:23,700 --> 02:48:25,440
nor the past pains thee,

4493
02:48:25,620 --> 02:48:26,800
but only the present.

4494
02:48:27,380 --> 02:48:29,420
But this is reduced to a very little,

4495
02:48:29,680 --> 02:48:31,740
if thou only circumscribest it,

4496
02:48:31,960 --> 02:48:33,300
and chidest thy mind,

4497
02:48:33,560 --> 02:48:35,200
if it is unable to hold out

4498
02:48:35,200 --> 02:48:36,220
against even this.

4499
02:48:36,660 --> 02:48:38,880
Does panthea or pergamos

4500
02:48:38,880 --> 02:48:40,540
now sit by the tomb of Verus?

4501
02:48:41,060 --> 02:48:43,020
Does sureus or diatomus

4502
02:48:43,020 --> 02:48:44,320
sit by the tomb of Hadrian?

4503
02:48:45,060 --> 02:48:46,160
That would be ridiculous.

4504
02:48:47,200 --> 02:48:49,360
Well, suppose they did sit there,

4505
02:48:49,580 --> 02:48:51,220
would the dead be conscious of it?

4506
02:48:51,440 --> 02:48:52,900
And if the dead were conscious,

4507
02:48:53,360 --> 02:48:54,440
would they be pleased?

4508
02:48:54,940 --> 02:48:56,160
And if they were pleased,

4509
02:48:56,640 --> 02:48:58,200
would that make them immortal?

4510
02:48:58,940 --> 02:49:01,040
Was it not in the order of destiny

4511
02:49:01,040 --> 02:49:02,580
that these persons too

4512
02:49:02,580 --> 02:49:04,240
should first become old women

4513
02:49:04,240 --> 02:49:05,260
and old men,

4514
02:49:05,340 --> 02:49:06,380
and then die?

4515
02:49:06,820 --> 02:49:08,040
What then would those do

4516
02:49:08,040 --> 02:49:09,300
after these were dead?

4517
02:49:09,620 --> 02:49:12,160
All this is foul smell and blood in a bag.

4518
02:49:13,240 --> 02:49:14,580
If thou canst see sharp,

4519
02:49:15,140 --> 02:49:16,360
look and judge wisely,

4520
02:49:16,640 --> 02:49:17,460
says the philosopher.

4521
02:49:18,420 --> 02:49:20,740
In the constitution of the rational animal,

4522
02:49:21,280 --> 02:49:23,560
I see no virtue which is opposed to justice,

4523
02:49:23,920 --> 02:49:25,600
but I see a virtue which is opposed

4524
02:49:25,600 --> 02:49:26,600
to love of pleasure,

4525
02:49:27,060 --> 02:49:28,540
and that is temperance.

4526
02:49:28,900 --> 02:49:31,040
If thou takest away thy opinion

4527
02:49:31,040 --> 02:49:33,640
about that which appears to give thee pain,

4528
02:49:34,100 --> 02:49:37,660
thou thyself standest in imperfect security.

4529
02:49:40,120 --> 02:49:41,340
Who is this self?

4530
02:49:42,000 --> 02:49:42,920
The reason.

4531
02:49:45,200 --> 02:49:47,300
But if any other part of thee suffers,

4532
02:49:47,900 --> 02:49:50,320
let it have its own opinion about itself,

4533
02:49:54,190 --> 02:49:57,390
and something else also is equally an impediment

4534
02:49:57,390 --> 02:49:59,950
and an evil to the constitution of plans.

4535
02:50:01,230 --> 02:50:03,730
So then, that which is a hindrance

4536
02:50:03,730 --> 02:50:05,870
to the intelligence is an evil

4537
02:50:05,870 --> 02:50:07,250
to the intelligent nature.

4538
02:50:10,880 --> 02:50:14,140
Does pain or sensuous pleasure affect thee?

4539
02:50:14,820 --> 02:50:16,720
The senses will look to that.

4540
02:50:22,320 --> 02:50:25,760
If, indeed, thou wast making this effort,

4541
02:50:26,360 --> 02:50:28,200
absolutely, unconditionally,

4542
02:50:28,380 --> 02:50:29,820
or without any reservation,

4543
02:50:30,380 --> 02:50:32,300
certainly this obstacle is an evil

4544
02:50:32,300 --> 02:50:34,460
to thee considered as a rational animal.

4545
02:50:34,740 --> 02:50:36,800
But if thou takest into consideration

4546
02:50:36,800 --> 02:50:38,600
the usual course of things,

4547
02:50:39,080 --> 02:50:40,840
thou hast not yet been injured,

4548
02:50:41,080 --> 02:50:42,300
nor even impeded.

4549
02:50:48,480 --> 02:50:50,080
When it has been made a sphere,

4550
02:50:50,500 --> 02:50:51,960
it continues a sphere.

4551
02:50:53,210 --> 02:50:55,830
It is not fit that I should give myself pain,

4552
02:50:56,030 --> 02:50:58,490
for I have never intentionally given pain

4553
02:50:58,490 --> 02:50:59,430
even to another.

4554
02:51:00,600 --> 02:51:02,720
Different things delight different people,

4555
02:51:03,200 --> 02:51:04,600
but it is my delight to keep

4556
02:51:04,600 --> 02:51:06,060
the ruling faculty sound,

4557
02:51:06,440 --> 02:51:08,620
without turning away either from any man

4558
02:51:08,620 --> 02:51:10,180
or from any of the things

4559
02:51:10,180 --> 02:51:11,160
which happen to men.

4560
02:51:11,620 --> 02:51:13,900
But looking at, and receiving all

4561
02:51:13,900 --> 02:51:16,320
with welcome eyes, and using everything

4562
02:51:16,320 --> 02:51:17,700
according to its value,

4563
02:51:18,260 --> 02:51:20,760
see that thou secure this present time

4564
02:51:20,760 --> 02:51:21,640
to thyself.

4565
02:51:22,000 --> 02:51:24,560
For those who rather pursue posthumous fame,

4566
02:51:25,240 --> 02:51:27,900
do consider that the men of after time

4567
02:51:27,900 --> 02:51:30,480
will be exactly and such as these

4568
02:51:30,480 --> 02:51:32,200
whom they cannot bear now.

4569
02:51:33,960 --> 02:51:36,160
And what is it in any way to thee

4570
02:51:36,160 --> 02:51:37,780
if these men of after time

4571
02:51:37,780 --> 02:51:39,240
utter this or that sound,

4572
02:51:39,660 --> 02:51:41,740
or have this or that opinion about thee?

4573
02:51:44,440 --> 02:51:46,500
Take me and cast me where thou wilt,

4574
02:51:46,760 --> 02:51:49,240
for there I shall keep my divine part tranquil,

4575
02:51:49,480 --> 02:51:50,700
that is, content,

4576
02:51:51,020 --> 02:51:52,920
if it can feel and act conformably

4577
02:51:52,920 --> 02:51:54,340
to its proper constitution.

4578
02:51:54,580 --> 02:51:56,220
Is this change of place?

4579
02:51:59,960 --> 02:52:01,780
Nothing can happen to any man

4580
02:52:01,780 --> 02:52:03,360
which is not a human accident,

4581
02:52:03,360 --> 02:52:05,700
nor to an ox which is not according

4582
02:52:05,700 --> 02:52:07,040
to the nature of an ox,

4583
02:52:07,240 --> 02:52:09,100
nor to a vine which is not,

4584
02:52:09,440 --> 02:52:11,220
according to the nature of a vine,

4585
02:52:11,480 --> 02:52:14,320
nor to a stone which is not proper to a stone.

4586
02:52:14,600 --> 02:52:17,140
If, then, there happens to each thing,

4587
02:52:17,340 --> 02:52:19,440
both what is usual and natural,

4588
02:52:19,880 --> 02:52:21,420
why shouldst thou complain?

4589
02:52:22,100 --> 02:52:24,000
For the common nature brings nothing,

4590
02:52:24,180 --> 02:52:25,780
which may not be borne by thee.

4591
02:52:26,180 --> 02:52:28,780
If thou art pained by any external thing,

4592
02:52:29,020 --> 02:52:31,120
it is not this thing that disturbs thee,

4593
02:52:31,380 --> 02:52:33,080
but thy own judgment about it.

4594
02:52:33,680 --> 02:52:37,360
And it is in thy power to wipe out this judgment now.

4595
02:52:37,780 --> 02:52:40,880
But if anything in thy own disposition gives thee pain,

4596
02:52:41,380 --> 02:52:43,640
who hinders thee from correcting thy opinion?

4597
02:52:44,100 --> 02:52:46,100
And even if thou art pained,

4598
02:52:46,120 --> 02:52:48,460
because thou art not doing some particular thing,

4599
02:52:48,640 --> 02:52:50,160
which seems to thee to be right,

4600
02:52:50,600 --> 02:52:53,200
why dost thou not rather act than complain?

4601
02:52:53,640 --> 02:52:56,180
But some insuperable obstacle is in the way.

4602
02:52:56,540 --> 02:52:57,860
Do not be grieved, then,

4603
02:52:57,860 --> 02:52:59,560
for the cause of its not being done

4604
02:52:59,560 --> 02:53:00,800
depends not on thee.

4605
02:53:01,410 --> 02:53:03,230
But it is not worth while to live

4606
02:53:03,230 --> 02:53:04,490
if this cannot be done.

4607
02:53:04,950 --> 02:53:07,650
Take thy departure, then, from life contentedly,

4608
02:53:07,850 --> 02:53:09,850
just as he dies who is in full activity,

4609
02:53:10,050 --> 02:53:12,570
and well pleased too with the things which are obstacles.

4610
02:53:13,050 --> 02:53:16,210
Remember that the ruling faculty is invincible,

4611
02:53:16,810 --> 02:53:20,650
when and self-collected it is satisfied with itself,

4612
02:53:21,110 --> 02:53:24,570
if it does nothing, which it does not choose to do,

4613
02:53:24,830 --> 02:53:27,630
even if it resists from mere obstinancy.

4614
02:53:29,080 --> 02:53:32,200
What, then, will it be when it forms a judgment

4615
02:53:32,200 --> 02:53:35,540
about anything aided by reason and deliberately?

4616
02:53:36,220 --> 02:53:39,600
Therefore the mind which is free from passions is a citadel,

4617
02:53:40,040 --> 02:53:42,860
for man has nothing more secure to which he can fly.

4618
02:53:47,360 --> 02:53:49,700
Say nothing more to thyself

4619
02:53:49,700 --> 02:53:51,960
than what the first appearances report.

4620
02:53:58,070 --> 02:54:00,190
I see that my child is sick.

4621
02:54:00,670 --> 02:54:04,350
I do see, but that he is in danger I do not see.

4622
02:54:08,440 --> 02:54:09,920
Cucumber is bitter.

4623
02:54:10,920 --> 02:54:11,740
Throw it away.

4624
02:54:12,600 --> 02:54:14,120
There are briars in the road.

4625
02:54:14,120 --> 02:54:15,880
Turn aside from them.

4626
02:54:16,300 --> 02:54:17,200
This is enough.

4627
02:54:18,300 --> 02:54:22,140
Do not add, and why were such things made in the world?

4628
02:54:22,950 --> 02:54:26,470
For thou wilt be ridiculed by a man who is acquainted with nature,

4629
02:54:27,030 --> 02:54:30,010
as thou wouldst be ridiculed by a carpenter and shoemaker,

4630
02:54:30,960 --> 02:54:34,440
if thou didst find fault because thou seest in their workshop.

4631
02:54:35,000 --> 02:54:37,800
Shavings and cuttings from the things which they make.

4632
02:54:38,220 --> 02:54:40,420
You need to add some text for me to talk,

4633
02:54:41,020 --> 02:54:42,660
and yet they have places into which

4634
02:54:42,660 --> 02:54:44,960
they can throw these shavings and cuttings,

4635
02:54:44,960 --> 02:54:47,720
and the universal nature has no external space.

4636
02:54:48,160 --> 02:54:52,360
But the wondrous part of her art is that though she has circumscribed herself,

4637
02:54:52,900 --> 02:54:57,020
everything within her which appears to decay and to grow old and to be useless,

4638
02:54:57,380 --> 02:55:01,400
she changes into herself and again makes other new things from.

4639
02:55:01,960 --> 02:55:06,320
These vary same, so that she requires neither substance from without,

4640
02:55:06,700 --> 02:55:10,360
nor wants a place into which she may cast not which decays.

4641
02:55:10,360 --> 02:55:16,200
She is content then with her own space and her own matter and her own art.

4642
02:55:20,460 --> 02:55:24,300
Suppose that men kill thee, cut thee in pieces, curse thee.

4643
02:55:25,310 --> 02:55:28,870
What then can these things do to prevent thy mind from remaining pure,

4644
02:55:29,270 --> 02:55:30,890
wise, sober, just?

4645
02:55:31,310 --> 02:55:36,730
For instance, if a man should stand by a limpid pure spring and curse it,

4646
02:55:36,970 --> 02:55:39,470
the spring never ceases sending up potable water,

4647
02:55:39,470 --> 02:55:45,430
and if he should cast clay into it or filth, it will speedily disperse them

4648
02:55:45,430 --> 02:55:48,390
and wash them out and will not be at all polluted.

4649
02:55:48,990 --> 02:55:54,430
How then shalt thou possess a perpetual fountain and not a mere well?

4650
02:55:55,650 --> 02:56:01,570
By forming thyself hourly to freedom, conjoined with contentment, simplicity,

4651
02:56:01,970 --> 02:56:06,450
and modesty, he who does not know what the world is,

4652
02:56:06,450 --> 02:56:13,090
does not know where he is, and he who does not know for what purpose the world exists,

4653
02:56:13,590 --> 02:56:17,370
does not know who he is, nor what the world is.

4654
02:56:21,610 --> 02:56:26,750
But he who has failed in any one of these things could not even say for what purpose he

4655
02:56:26,750 --> 02:56:32,250
exists himself. What then dost thou think of him who avoids or seeks the praise of those

4656
02:56:32,250 --> 02:56:37,490
who applaud, of men who know not either where they are or who they are?

4657
02:56:41,650 --> 02:56:46,550
Dost thou wish to be praised by a man who curses himself thrice every hour?

4658
02:56:46,910 --> 02:56:50,450
Whatst thou wish to please a man who does not please himself?

4659
02:56:54,360 --> 02:56:58,100
Does a man please himself who repents of nearly everything that he does?

4660
02:56:58,760 --> 02:57:04,020
No longer let thy breathing, only act in concert with the air which surrounds thee,

4661
02:57:04,360 --> 02:57:08,700
but let thy intelligence also now be in harmony with the nine intelligence

4662
02:57:08,700 --> 02:57:14,580
which embraces all things, for the intelligent power is no less diffused in all parts

4663
02:57:14,580 --> 02:57:18,880
and pervades all things for him who is willing to draw it to him

4664
02:57:18,880 --> 02:57:22,580
than the aerial power for him who is able to respire it.

4665
02:57:23,320 --> 02:57:26,440
Generally wickedness does no harm at all to the universe,

4666
02:57:26,960 --> 02:57:30,460
and particularly the wickedness of one man does no harm to another.

4667
02:57:31,080 --> 02:57:35,360
It is only harmful to him who has it in his power to be released from it

4668
02:57:35,360 --> 02:57:43,400
as soon as he shall choose. To my own free will,

4669
02:57:43,720 --> 02:57:48,040
the free will of my neighbor is just as indifferent as his poor breath and flesh.

4670
02:57:48,600 --> 02:57:51,720
For though we are made especially for the sake of one another,

4671
02:57:52,530 --> 02:57:56,510
still the ruling power of each of us has its own office.

4672
02:57:59,440 --> 02:58:03,940
The sun appears to be poured down, and in all directions indeed it is diffused,

4673
02:58:04,600 --> 02:58:08,760
yet it is not effused. For this diffusion is extension.

4674
02:58:09,500 --> 02:58:12,960
Accordingly its rays are called extensions because they are extended.

4675
02:58:13,580 --> 02:58:15,800
You need to add some text for me to talk.

4676
02:58:16,420 --> 02:58:21,840
But one may judge what kind of a thing a ray is if he looks at the sun's light

4677
02:58:21,840 --> 02:58:27,380
passing through a narrow opening into a darkened room, for it is extended in a right line,

4678
02:58:27,580 --> 02:58:31,340
and as it were is divided when it meets with any solid body

4679
02:58:31,340 --> 02:58:34,440
which stands in the way and intercepts the air beyond.

4680
02:58:36,400 --> 02:58:43,430
But there, the light remains fixed. Such, then, ought to be the outpouring

4681
02:58:43,430 --> 02:58:48,370
and diffusion of the understanding, and it should in no way be an effusion,

4682
02:58:48,770 --> 02:58:53,230
but an extension, and it should make no violent or impetuous collision

4683
02:58:53,230 --> 02:58:57,570
with the obstacles which are in its way nor yet fall down,

4684
02:58:58,070 --> 02:59:01,930
but be fixed, and enlighten that which receives it.

4685
02:59:02,130 --> 02:59:08,050
For a body will deprive itself of the illumination if it does not admit it.

4686
02:59:11,910 --> 02:59:17,290
Ye who fears death either fears the loss of sensation, or a different kind of sensation,

4687
02:59:17,630 --> 02:59:21,390
or a different kind of sensation. But if thou shalt have no sensation,

4688
02:59:21,770 --> 02:59:26,070
neither wilt thou feel any harm, and if thou shalt acquire another kind of sensation,

4689
02:59:26,490 --> 02:59:29,210
thou wilt be a different kind of living being, and thou wilt.

4690
02:59:29,990 --> 02:59:38,200
Men exist for the sake of one another. Teach them, then, or bear with them.

4691
02:59:38,780 --> 02:59:43,540
