In my sickness my conversation was not about my bodily sufferings,

4887
03:21:37,090 --> 03:21:41,510
nor, says he, did I talk on such subjects to those who visited me.

4888
03:21:43,070 --> 03:21:46,590
But I continue to discourse on the nature of things as before.

4889
03:21:48,360 --> 03:21:58,780
Keeping to this main point, Infine, turn thy prayers this way, and see what comes.

4890
03:22:03,080 --> 03:22:05,160
You need to add some text for me to talk.

4891
03:22:05,160 --> 03:22:08,360
Do, then, the same that he did both in sickness.

4892
03:22:10,130 --> 03:22:17,370
If thou art sick, and in any other circumstances, for never to desert philosophy

4893
03:22:17,370 --> 03:22:23,290
in any events that may befall us, nor to hold trifling talk either with an ignorant man,

4894
03:22:23,730 --> 03:22:29,500
or with one unacquainted with nature, is a principle of all schools of philosophy.

4895
03:22:31,360 --> 03:22:34,180
But to be intent only on that which thou art now,

4896
03:22:34,180 --> 03:22:38,580
doing, and on, the instrument by which thou doest it.

4897
03:22:38,980 --> 03:22:44,300
When thou art offended with any man's shameless conduct, immediately ask thyself,

4898
03:22:44,960 --> 03:22:48,980
Is it possible, then, that shameless men should not be in the world?

4899
03:22:53,070 --> 03:22:59,130
For this man also is one of those shameless men who must of necessity be in the world.

4900
03:23:00,060 --> 03:23:04,620
Let the same considerations be present to thy mind in the case of the knave,

4901
03:23:04,620 --> 03:23:10,080
and the faithless man, and of every man who does wrong in any way.

4902
03:23:10,860 --> 03:23:15,220
For at the same time that thou dost remind thyself that it is impossible

4903
03:23:15,220 --> 03:23:20,840
that such kind of men should not exist, thou wilt become more kindly disposed

4904
03:23:20,840 --> 03:23:22,640
towards every one individually.

4905
03:23:23,260 --> 03:23:28,280
It is useful to perceive this, too, immediately when the occasion arises,

4906
03:23:28,600 --> 03:23:32,960
what virtue nature has given to man to oppose to every wrongful act.

4907
03:23:32,960 --> 03:23:38,020
For she has given to man, as an antidote against the stupid man,

4908
03:23:38,420 --> 03:23:42,840
mildness, and against another kind of man, some other power.

4909
03:23:46,800 --> 03:23:49,780
And in all cases it is possible for thee to correct,

4910
03:23:50,300 --> 03:23:52,620
by teaching the man who is gone astray.

4911
03:23:53,140 --> 03:23:57,640
For every man who errs misses his object, and is gone astray.

4912
03:23:58,880 --> 03:24:01,140
Besides, wherein hast thou been injured?

4913
03:24:01,140 --> 03:24:06,900
For thou wilt find that no one among those against whom thou art irritated

4914
03:24:06,900 --> 03:24:10,760
has done anything by which thy mind could be made worse.

4915
03:24:11,480 --> 03:24:16,260
But that which is evil to thee, and harmful, has its foundation only in the mind.

4916
03:24:16,860 --> 03:24:19,300
And what harm is done, or what is there?

4917
03:24:19,740 --> 03:24:24,840
Strange, if the man who has not been instructed does the acts of an uninstructed man.

4918
03:24:27,640 --> 03:24:31,480
Consider, whether thou shouldst not rather blame thyself,

4919
03:24:31,480 --> 03:24:35,720
because thou didst not expect such a man to err in such a way.

4920
03:24:36,020 --> 03:24:38,860
For thou hast means, given thee by thy reason,

4921
03:24:39,520 --> 03:24:42,520
to suppose that it was likely that he would commit this error,

4922
03:24:42,920 --> 03:24:46,740
and yet thou hast forgotten, and art amazed that he has erred.

4923
03:24:53,450 --> 03:24:57,190
But most of all, when thou blamest a man as faithless or ungrateful,

4924
03:24:57,530 --> 03:25:01,130
turn to thyself, for the fault is manifestly thy own.

4925
03:25:01,750 --> 03:25:07,050
Whether thou didst trust that a man who had such a disposition would keep his promise.

4926
03:25:07,880 --> 03:25:12,560
Or when conferring thy kindness, thou didst not confer it absolutely,

4927
03:25:13,590 --> 03:25:18,210
nor yet in such way as to have received from thy very act all the profit.

4928
03:25:19,690 --> 03:25:23,750
For what more dost thou want when thou hast done a man a service?

4929
03:25:24,610 --> 03:25:29,030
Art thou not content that thou hast done something conformable to thy nature,

4930
03:25:29,490 --> 03:25:32,610
and dost thou seek to be paid for it?

4931
03:25:36,140 --> 03:25:38,280
You need to add some text for me to talk.

4932
03:25:38,380 --> 03:25:41,920
For as these members are formed for a particular purpose,

4933
03:25:42,260 --> 03:25:46,620
and by working according to their several constitutions, obtain what is their own.

4934
03:25:50,260 --> 03:25:55,420
Wilt thou then, my soul, never be good and simple, and one and naked,

4935
03:25:55,760 --> 03:25:58,440
more manifest than the body which surrounds thee?

4936
03:25:59,320 --> 03:26:02,680
Wilt thou never enjoy an affectionate and contented disposition?

4937
03:26:03,400 --> 03:26:07,920
Wilt thou never be full, and without a want of any kind,

4938
03:26:07,920 --> 03:26:12,980
longing for nothing more, nor desiring anything, either animate or inanimate,

4939
03:26:13,180 --> 03:26:17,020
for the enjoyment of? You need to add some text for me to talk.

4940
03:26:17,640 --> 03:26:20,520
But wilt thou be satisfied with thy present condition,

4941
03:26:20,960 --> 03:26:23,040
and pleased with all that is about thee?

4942
03:26:24,170 --> 03:26:29,690
And wilt thou convince thyself that thou hast everything, and that it comes from the gods?

4943
03:26:30,470 --> 03:26:35,410
That everything is well for thee, and will be well whatever shall please them,

4944
03:26:38,960 --> 03:26:41,260
good and just and beautiful?

4945
03:26:41,540 --> 03:26:46,240
Which generates and holds together all things, and contains and embraces all things,

4946
03:26:46,360 --> 03:26:49,220
which are dissolved for the production of other like things?

4947
03:26:49,880 --> 03:26:53,720
Nor yet desiring time, wherein thou shalt have longer enjoyment,

4948
03:26:54,140 --> 03:26:59,720
or place, or pleasant climate, or society of men with whom thou mayest live in harmony.

4949
03:27:00,620 --> 03:27:04,900
Wilt thou never be such that thou shalt so dwell in community with gods and men,

4950
03:27:05,200 --> 03:27:08,540
as neither to find fault with them at all, nor to be condemned by them?

4951
03:27:09,180 --> 03:27:14,420
Observe what thy nature requires, so far as thou art governed by nature only.

4952
03:27:18,850 --> 03:27:22,770
And all this thou mayest allow thyself, if thy nature,

4953
03:27:23,090 --> 03:27:27,390
so far as thou art a rational animal, shall not be made worse by it.

4954
03:27:27,970 --> 03:27:33,410
And but the rational animal is consequently also a political, social animal.

4955
03:27:34,680 --> 03:27:38,240
Use these rules then, and trouble thyself about nothing else.

4956
03:27:38,240 --> 03:27:44,420
Everything which happens, either happens in such wise as thou art formed by nature to bear it,

4957
03:27:44,700 --> 03:27:48,120
or as thou art not formed by nature to bear it.

4958
03:27:50,670 --> 03:27:55,550
But if it happens in such wise as thou art not formed by nature to bear it,

4959
03:27:55,730 --> 03:27:59,330
do not complain, for it will perish after it has consumed thee.

4960
03:27:59,750 --> 03:28:04,330
Remember, however, that thou art formed by nature to bear everything,

4961
03:28:04,950 --> 03:28:10,070
with respect to which it depends on thy own opinion to make it endurable and tolerable.

4962
03:28:10,350 --> 03:28:15,970
By thinking that it is either thy interest or thy think, if a man is mistaken,

4963
03:28:16,550 --> 03:28:19,250
instruct him kindly, and show him his error.

4964
03:28:19,840 --> 03:28:24,460
But if thou art not able, blame thyself, or blame not even thyself.

4965
03:28:25,040 --> 03:28:28,440
Whatever may happen to thee, it was prepared for thee from all eternity,

4966
03:28:28,900 --> 03:28:32,880
and the implication of causes was from eternity spinning the thread of thy being,

4967
03:28:33,080 --> 03:28:35,000
and of that which is incident to it.

4968
03:28:35,380 --> 03:28:39,780
Whether the universe is a concourse of atoms, or nature is a system,

4969
03:28:40,380 --> 03:28:46,200
let this first be established, that I am a part of the whole which is governed by nature.

4970
03:28:50,670 --> 03:28:56,770
For remembering this, inasmuch as I am a part, I shall be discontented with none of the things

4971
03:28:56,770 --> 03:29:02,960
which are assigned to me out of the whole, for nothing is injurious to the part,

4972
03:29:03,950 --> 03:29:09,430
if it is for the advantage of the whole, for the whole contains nothing which is not

4973
03:29:09,430 --> 03:29:13,850
for its advantage, and all natures indeed have this common principle,

4974
03:29:14,530 --> 03:29:17,070
but the nature of the universe has this principle.

4975
03:29:18,300 --> 03:29:26,090
Besides, that it cannot be incompelled even by any external cause to generate anything harmful

4976
03:29:26,090 --> 03:29:31,850
to itself. By remembering then, that I am a part of such a whole, I shall be content with

4977
03:29:31,850 --> 03:29:37,110
everything that happens, and inasmuch as I am in a manner intimately related to the parts

4978
03:29:37,110 --> 03:29:44,860
which are of the same kind with myself, I shall do nothing unsocial, but I shall rather direct

4979
03:29:44,860 --> 03:29:53,370
myself to the things which are of the same kind with myself, and I shall turn all my efforts

4980
03:29:53,370 --> 03:29:59,990
to the common interest, and divert them from the contrary. Now, if these things are done so,

4981
03:30:00,190 --> 03:30:06,370
life must flow on happily, just as thou mayst observe that the life of a citizen is happy,

4982
03:30:06,370 --> 03:30:11,310
who continues a course of action which is advantageous to his fellow citizens,

4983
03:30:11,570 --> 03:30:14,810
and is content with whatever the state may assign to him.

4984
03:30:15,070 --> 03:30:20,430
The parts of the whole everything, I mean, which is naturally comprehended in the universe,

4985
03:30:20,830 --> 03:30:30,140
must of necessity perish. But let this be understood in this sense, that they must

4986
03:30:30,140 --> 03:30:36,340
undergo change, but if this is naturally both an evil and a necessity for the parts,

4987
03:30:36,340 --> 03:30:42,480
the whole would not continue to exist in a good condition, the parts being subject to change and

4988
03:30:42,480 --> 03:30:50,720
constituted so as to perish in various ways. For whether did Nature herself design to do evil

4989
03:30:50,720 --> 03:30:56,520
to the things which are parts of herself, and to make them subject to evil and of necessity

4990
03:30:56,520 --> 03:31:02,860
fall into evil, or have such results happened without her knowing it? You need to add some

4991
