text for me to talk. But if a man should even drop the term Nature as an efficient power,

4992
03:31:09,490 --> 03:31:16,260
and should speak of these things as natural, even then it would be ridiculous to affirm at

4993
03:31:16,260 --> 03:31:21,040
the same time that the parts of the whole are in their nature subject to change,

4994
03:31:21,600 --> 03:31:25,640
and at the same time to be surprised or vexed as if something were happening

4995
03:31:25,640 --> 03:31:31,600
contrary to Nature, particularly as the dissolution of things is in to those things

4996
03:31:31,600 --> 03:31:38,160
of which each thing is composed, both these suppositions indeed are incredible. For there

4997
03:31:38,160 --> 03:31:42,220
is either a dispersion of the elements out of which everything has been compounded,

4998
03:31:42,440 --> 03:31:46,620
or a change from the solid to and the earthy and from the airy to the aerial,

4999
03:31:47,040 --> 03:31:52,320
so that these parts are taken back into the universal reason, whether this at certain periods

5000
03:31:52,320 --> 03:31:58,400
is consumed by fire or renewed by. And do not imagine that the solid and the airy part

5001
03:31:58,400 --> 03:32:07,040
belong to thee from the time of generation. This, then, which has received the accretion,

5002
03:32:07,120 --> 03:32:12,460
changes, not that which thy mother brought forth. But suppose that this which thy mother

5003
03:32:12,460 --> 03:32:17,760
brought forth implicates thee very much with that other part, which has the peculiar quality

5004
03:32:17,760 --> 03:32:23,820
of change. This is nothing, in fact, in the way of objection to what is said. When thou hast

5005
03:32:23,820 --> 03:32:31,340
assumed these names, good, modest, true, rational, a man of equanimity and magnanimous,

5006
03:32:31,820 --> 03:32:36,880
take care that thou dost not change these names, and if thou shouldst lose them.

5007
03:32:39,700 --> 03:32:44,700
And remember that the term rational was intended to signify a discriminating attention

5008
03:32:44,700 --> 03:32:49,540
to every several thing, and freedom from negligence of the things which are assigned

5009
03:32:49,540 --> 03:32:55,160
to thee by the common nature, and that magnanimity is the elevation of the intelligent

5010
03:32:55,160 --> 03:33:01,480
part above the pleasurable or painful sensations of the flesh, and above that poor thing called

5011
03:33:01,480 --> 03:33:09,070
fame, and death, and all such things. For to continue to be such as thou hast his or two

5012
03:33:09,070 --> 03:33:15,830
been, and to be Tom in pieces and defiled in such a life, is the character of a very stupid

5013
03:33:15,830 --> 03:33:23,500
man, and one over fond of his life. And like those half devoured fighters with wild beasts,

5014
03:33:23,500 --> 03:33:28,860
who though covered with wounds and gore, still entreat to be kept to the following day,

5015
03:33:29,140 --> 03:33:34,500
though they will be exposed. If then thou maintainest thyself in the possession of

5016
03:33:34,500 --> 03:33:39,580
these names, without desiring to be called by these names by others, thou wilt be another

5017
03:33:39,580 --> 03:33:45,600
person and wilt enter on another life. Therefore, fix thyself in the possession of

5018
03:33:45,600 --> 03:33:51,960
these few names, and if thou art able to abide in them, abide as if thou wast removed

5019
03:33:51,960 --> 03:33:58,580
